title: wiener wrap
directions: Cut hot dogs in 3 pieces.
Wrap bacon around hot dogs and hold with toothpick.
Lay in a crock-pot.
Pour bag of brown sugar over top.
Put pot on high until sugar melts, then turn on low and cook for 2 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms, italian style
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems and chop fine.
Remove casing from sausage and put meat in skillet with chopped stems, the garlic and 1 tablespoon oil.
Cook, breaking up meat with fork, until lightly browned.
Add 1 tablespoon oil, the parsley and cheese.
Fill mushroom cavities with the mixture, rounding up tops.
Place in shallow baking pan.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Cream the eggs and sugar together. Add oil alternately with dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven in a lined tube pan, greased and floured, or bake in a
long 9 x 13-inch pan. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: sicilian apricot cheese dessert
directions: Brush inside of dessert shells with rum.
Heat preserves until melted.
Brush on shells, reserving part of preserves.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce with sugar, vinegar and mustard until sugar is dissolved and set aside.
Beat egg slightly.
Add onion, crackers, beef, salt and 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture.
Combine lightly but thoroughly.
Shape meat into oval loaf in a bowl. Turn into shallow baking dish, keeping loaf shapely.
Pour on rest of sauce mixture.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: no bake dressing
directions: Bake cubes in 325° oven until dry and golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Melt butter in 4-quart Dutch oven or 4-quart saucepan with medium heat.
Add celery and onion and saute 10 minutes or until tender.
Do not brown.
Add parsley and cook 2 minutes (drain canned mushrooms).
Saute fresh mushrooms (reserve juice from can, enough water to make 2/3 cup).
Stir mushrooms, liquid chicken broth, sage and pepper into vegetables in pot.
Cook over high heat until it reaches boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in bread cubes (and nuts, if used).
Cover and let set 10 minutes.
Stir to fluff and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Spread thin on a pizza pan.
Top with jar of taco sauce.
Put vegetables and cheese on top.

title: party punch
directions: Mix soda and juice (reserve some for ice ring along with 1 package strawberries).
Add sherbet and strawberries (1 package). Chill before serving.
Add ice ring on serving.

title: stuffed mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Sprinkle raw mushroom caps with Accent and salt on both sides. Mix ground beef and other ingredients.
(The balls may be made ahead and frozen.)
Roll into 50 balls with cold, wet hands. Place into raw mushroom caps. Broil. When the meat is browned well, they are ready.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach as per directions on package; drain well.
Saute onions in margarine.
Add spinach.
Beat eggs.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, cheese, half and half and sauteed spinach; mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked deep dish pie shell or two 9-inch unbaked regular pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: taco layer dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of a large dish.
Stir together sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning.
Spread on top of beans. Peel and core avocados.
Blend avocados, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste until smooth.
Spread on top of taco seasoning mixture.
Layer tomatoes, olives, green onions and cheese.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oven fried chicken(this oven fried chicken is not exactly fried but good anyway.)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Coat each breast with butter flavored cooking spray; dredge in cereal mixture.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup white flour, wheat flour, yeast and salt; mix well.
Heat milk, water, honey and shortening until warm (shortening does not need to melt).
Add to flour mixture.
Add egg.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in remaining white flour to make firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until light and doubled (about 1 hour).
Punch down dough and divide in 2. On floured surface roll or pat into rectangle.
Start with short side and roll up tightly.
Pinch edges and ends to seal.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (about 1/2 hour).
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from pans and cool.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rio grande chicken
directions: Brown the rice in 2 tablespoons oil over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Add tomato pieces, onion and garlic to rice. Cook 5 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Brown chicken in remaining oil in large pot.
Add rice mixture, bouillon and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 40 minutes or until rice and chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: german bean soup
directions: Saut onion in 1 tablespoon bacon drippings. Add potatoes, carrots, green beans, parsley, sage, hot sauce and water. Bring to a boil; cover and
simmer 20 minutes. Take off heat and add sausage, undrained Northern beans and bacon pieces.

title: korean beef skewer
directions: Cut the beef into thin slices across width of steak.
Cut the green onion into 2-inch lengths.
Cut the mushrooms in half. Skewer the meat, onion and mushroom alternately on skewers.
Mix the soy sauce, sugar, sesame seed, sesame oil, black pepper, garlic and rice wine to make the seasoning sauce.
Pour on seasoning and leave 5 minutes.
Put little bit oil on frypan and fry them until desired doneness.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Skin chicken; roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Remove chicken and place in 3 or 4-quart casserole dish.
Brown onion in skillet and pour rice over chicken in casserole dish.
Add tomatoes, water and onion.
Cover tightly with tinfoil.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: breakfast before
directions: Place bread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat all remaining ingredients together.
Pour over bread.
Set in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, walnuts, sugar and margarine with pastry blender or fork until crumbly.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake in a
350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter or margarine onto the bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over melted butter.
Sprinkle nuts evenly over crumbs.
Scatter chocolate pieces over nuts. Sprinkle coconut evenly over chocolate pieces.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth just to boiling.
Stir in cornstarch (if used). Stir soup until it thickens (if cornstarch is used, about 1 minute).
Add sherry; stir.
Gently stir in egg.
Leave shreds of egg.
Remove from heat.
Garnish with scallions.
Serve immediately.
Serves 3.

title: cucumber vinaigrette salad(gurkensalat)
directions: Wash cucumbers and peel; slice very thin.
Place in glass or china bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour or longer. Squeeze liquid out of cucumbers.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Mix and serve.
Serves 4.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple; heat juice to boiling and pour over jello. Add cold water and cream cheese and beat with beater until well blended.
Add pineapple, nuts and celery.

title: artichokes with curry-mustard dip(servings:  4)
directions: Clean and trim artichokes.
Bring stock and wine to boil. Lower heat and steam artichokes covered for 40 minutes.

title: simple peach cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, peaches and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mock steak
directions: Mix hamburger, corn flakes or rice, milk, salt, pepper and egg together.
Should be sloppy.
Spoon mixture into hot fat in little patties.
Brown on both sides.
Put patties into large casserole dish.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Slice potatoes into baking dish and add meat/onion mixture.
Pour soup over meat/potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: sausage bake
directions: Cook sausage until almost brown. Add onion & celery and cook until tender. Remove and place into a 9 in. greased pan. Top with spaghetti. Combine soup & milk. Add eggs & cheese. Pour over spaghetti. Combine bread crumbs & butter. Sprinkle on casserole. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight and rinse in a.m.
Put in crock-pot and cover with water.
Add all ingredients except sausage.
Cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Put sausage in during last hour of cooking.
Cook rice as directed.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a single layer 13-inch x 9-inch pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Combine cake mix, water, oil, and eggs. Mix at low speed or hand stir at high speed or hand beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Put the stuff in the bowl as you go down the line.
Don't put the cookie cutter or stir thing or sprinkles or chocolate things in the bowl.
Stir for 3 minutes.
Put dough on pan and roll it out. Cut dough using cookie cutters.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Take out of oven.
Put on sprinkles or chocolate things.
Let them cool off. Eat them!

title: 12 minute peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, raw peanuts and pinch of salt together in glass bowl.
Cook on High in microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 minutes.
Stir and add butter; stir completely.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Stir and add vanilla and soda.
Turn onto greased cookie sheet.
Cool, then break into pieces.

title: mashed, smashed and whipped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, either peeled or not, for 10 minutes.
Drain them and let cool. Cut them into strips, crinkles or however you like.
Preheat oven to 375° and spray cookie sheet with Pam. Place potatoes on sheet so they do not touch.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: butter rich almond torte
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix for topping.
To remainder of mix, add softened butter and egg.
Blend and pat into bottom of pan.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add oil, sugar and egg.
When mixed well, add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet. Bake at 300° until done.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dip pieces of chicken in melted margarine, then in dry mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: dressing for hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over Hawaiian chicken salad 1/2 hour before you serve.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, honey and flavoring thoroughly. Sift together flour, soda and salt and stir in.
Chill dough. Heat oven to 375° (quick moderate).
Roll dough out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, or until no imprint remains when touched lightly with finger.
When cool, ice and decorate as desired.
Makes about 5 dozen.
I make about 1000 of these for Christmas to give away.
I always double this recipe.
I will stir them up one day and put dough in refrigerator and bake them the next day.

title: chili in crock-pot
directions: Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion. Pour off grease.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low all day.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Dip breasts in melted butter.
Roll in mixture of cheese, bread crumbs and garlic salt.
Top with parsley in uncovered glass baking dish.
Pour unused butter over top of breasts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender for 30 seconds. Pour into greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife blade inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: gingerbread kids
directions: Beat sugar, shortening, molasses and water in a large bowl on low speed until blended. Beat on medium speed for 1 minute. Stir in remaining ingredients except raisins. Cover and refrigerate until chilled, 1 or 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough on a floured cloth until 1/4-inch thick. Cut with 5 to 8-inch cutters.
Bake on ungreased sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ice cream in plastic bag
directions: Put in plastic Ziploc bag.
In second bag, put approximately 15 cubes of ice and 6 teaspoons of table salt.
Freezes best if used with 1 cup of mix per bag.
Use 1 quart size bag for mix, 1 gallon size bag ice and salt.
Shake for 10 minutes.
Tastes like snow cream.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt well.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Chill 15 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch crusts.

title: five bean casserole
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in a large skillet, over medium heat, fry bacon and onion until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar, vinegar, celery salt, garlic salt, dry mustard and salt.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat. Stir in milk.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into creamed mixture and fold in blueberries.
Spoon into well buttered 9-inch square pan and smooth the top.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix sugar and milk; add Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Mix well together and add to shredded cabbage.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.
Makes one gallon. Remove from freezer an hour or so before serving.
Serve as a slush.

title: country fried pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops and mushrooms (use 1 tablespoon shortening if needed).
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water and thyme.
Add onions and carrots.
Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Makes 4 servings. Serve with noodles and tossed salad.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish in layers.
Sprinkle each layer with minced onion, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Add milk.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black bean soup
directions: Rinse beans in colander with running cold water and discard any stones or shriveled beans.
Place beans in stewpot and cover with water.
Heat to boiling and cook 3 minutes. Remove from heat, cover, and let soak for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans. Meanwhile, saute onions, bacon, and jalapeno.
Return beans to the pot with 8 c. water, add the sauteed mixture and the remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low, cover pot and simmer for several hours, or until beans are very
tender.
Serves 8-10.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Gradually add powdered sugar; blend thoroughly, then add pecans and vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together and work into sugar mixture.
Pinch off by teaspoonfuls. Roll in hands until pencil thin.
Form into crescent shapes and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. When cool, sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan; add green pepper, onion and celery.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and cook until it is bubbly.
Slowly add canned tomatoes, then coarsely chop with spoon.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, bay leaf and parsley.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf, then add Worcestershire sauce and shrimp.
Heat until shrimp are hot.
Serve over cooked rice.
Garnish with parsley and whole shrimp.

title: orange salad
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan; chill.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine the sugar, butter and milk in a saucepan, bring to a boil , continue to boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in chips, add marshmallow creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: butter bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in water to cover.
Drain.

title: chinese beef and rice
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir rice in oil over medium heat until golden brown.
Add salt, water, bouillon cubes and soy sauce.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in onions, celery, green pepper, mushrooms and beef.
Cover tightly; simmer 20 minutes longer or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: italian touch baked chicken
directions: Mix together oatmeal, Parmesan cheese, salt (optional), paprika and pepper.
Place oatmeal mixture in shallow dish.

title: aunt ann's bean dish
directions: Saute sausage, onions and celery until brown.
Drain and place in a large mixing bowl.
Add all the remaining ingredients plus 1 can of water.
Place in a casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Press all except 1 cup into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mash cream cheese until soft; beat in sugar and vanilla gradually.
Fold in whipped topping; drop by spoonfuls over crumb mixture.
Spread gently with spatula.
Spread blueberry filling evenly over cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup of graham crumbs.
Chill.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken slowly until meat is tender, adding salt while cooking.
Remove chicken, bone and cut up meat.
Strain broth and cook corn and celery until tender.
Return chicken to broth. Bring soup to a boil and add Rivels while stirring.
Boil slowly about 5 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, Karo syrup
and
water
in
a
boiler.
Stir together and pour in peanuts.
Cook
to
a
boil,
then reduce heat to medium.
Boil until
this mixture turns a golden brown and the peanuts burst open.
Pull spoon out of mixture to see if
a hard thread forms.
If so, this means it is ready.
Have aluminum foil
spread out on counter and butter this surface. After
a hard thread forms, take the boiler and add 1 heaping teaspoonful of
baking
soda to mixture and remove from heat, stirring
fast. When
it thickens and lightens in color, pour the mixture out onto the foil.
Spread so that the peanuts are one
layer
thick.
Let this cool completely and harden.
When cooled
completely,
break the
peanut
brittle
into smaller pieces.
This is great also made with pecans.

title: ham rolls (appetizer)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll crescent rolls into rectangle shape.
Combine olives, ham and cream cheese.
Spread the mixture onto the rectangle shapes and then roll them up.
Cut into 3 or 4 pieces.
Cook approximately 10 minutes.

title: quick divinity
directions: Combine icing mix, syrup and boiling water.
Beat on high speed for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and beat until stiff peaks form. Turn to low speed and beat in the confectioners sugar.
Fold in the nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Dry by turning pieces over once or twice.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 36 pieces.

title: almost homemade 7 layer cake
directions: Mix both cake mixes according to directions.
Cut seven 12 x 12-inch pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil, sprinkle them with sugar.
Spray cake pans with Pam cooking spray.
Pour 1 cup cake mix on each pan.
Bake.
Remove from oven and turn onto foil pieces.
When completely cooled, cover each layer with 1 tablespoon of frosting.
Stick layers and frost top and sides.
Tastes like Grandma's.

title: lori's hot chili
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic; drain and add salsa, tomato sauce, Ro-Tel, water, salt and seasoning pouch.
Bring to
a boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 18.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Brown onions after slicing in 1/4 cup butter.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, press crackers to make crust.
Place onions on top; sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour milk and eggs over top.
Also the other 1/4 cup butter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle another cup of crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix 4 dry ingredients well and add milk until smooth.
Melt margarine in iron skillet.
Add mixture and cook until desired consistency.
Serve on biscuits.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Cool.
Slice each layer and make 4 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and flavoring.
Add 1 1/2 packages coconut.
Mix and put between layers only.
Mix the remaining coconut and Cool Whip.
Frost top and sides of cake. Save some coconut to sprinkle on top.
Let stand several hours or overnight.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° until done.
Use any kind of icing or glaze.

title: fruit in snow
directions: Whisk and chill to blend.
Great over berries or melon.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling and dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Cool. Gently stir in ginger ale.
Blend drained pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Turn into a 9 x 12-inch flat dish and chill until firm.

title: mushroom enchiladas
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and heat in saucepan until cheese is melted.
Reserve 1/2 of soup mixture; mix ground beef and remaining soup mixture.
Roll inside tortilla and place side by side in pan.
Pour reserved soup mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: hearty oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.

title: crawfish stuffed bell peppers
directions: Melt margarine in aluminum skillet.
Chop each crawfish tail into several pieces and season well with Tony's.
Add crawfish, chopped vegetables and egg whites to the melted margarine.
Saute at least 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add bread crumbs to thicken the mixture.
Wash and core peppers, fill with crawfish mixture and top with bread crumbs.
Place peppers upright in casserole dish.
Cover bottom of the dish with chicken broth or water to which a teaspoon of granulated chicken bouillon has been added.
Bake in 300° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: venison ribs
directions: Boil ribs in water until tender (this removes the fat).
Take ribs from water and let cool.
Marinate in liquid smoke 1 to 2 hours.
Take out of marinade and sprinkle with pepper to taste. Prepare charcoal smoker to manufacturer's instructions.
When coals ash over, liberally add hickory chunks.
Fill drip pan with water and put ribs on and cook 1 hour per pound.
When finished, remove and let cool.
Brush sauce on ribs and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, take out and when at room temperature, put on barbecue grill. When sauce sets up, ribs are ready.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: delicious oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and raisins; cover and set aside. Cream brown sugar, butter and vanilla. Add the eggs, then the oats. Mix well and stir in dry ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and cocoa in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in oats, vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: festive pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a medium bowl, cut margarine into flour, with a pastry blender or a knife, until mixture looks like fine bread crumbs.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese, garlic powder, onion powder, basil, oregano and paprika.
Sprinkle cold water over mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Toss with a fork until dough gathers into a ball.
Divide dough into balls and refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie with cinnamon cream sauce
directions: Fill buttered 9-inch pie pan 2/3 full of apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden. Serve with Cinnamon Cream Sauce.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Boil slowly the milk and sugar. Just before reaching the soft ball stage, add the pecans. When soft ball stage is reached, remove and beat until creamy. Quickly, drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Cool completely before removing.

title: fried dough bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread in refrigerator overnight and at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Pinch off pieces of dough; stretch and drop in hot oil.
Fry on each side until golden brown.
(Oil hands before stretching bread for easier handling.)
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or eat plain.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Clean, core and shred cabbage.
Put the cabbage with water and salt in a heavy saucepan; cover and cook for 8 to 10 minutes. Cook the onion in margarine until golden.
Add the sugar, flour, water, vinegar, salt and pepper to the onion.
Cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Drain cabbage and add it to thickened sauce; mix well.
Heat the cabbage through.
Garnish with bacon bits.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham on aluminum foil.
Cover with mustard.
Pat brown sugar over the ham.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 4 to 6 hours, depending on size of ham.
Unwrap foil from top of ham and brown for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chow mein noodles; put in casserole; sprinkle top with cheese and chow mein noodles. Bake for 25 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the three ingredients well and pour onto greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Add 2 envelopes spaghetti sauce seasoning.
Add oregano, bottle of ketchup, celery, tomato paste, canned tomatoes, thyme, rosemary and garlic.
Add water.
Cook down approximately 2 hours on low heat uncovered.
Stir often.

title: veggie kabobs
directions: Trim through ends from large mushrooms and cut the zucchini into chunks.
Thread mushrooms, zucchini, onions, tomatoes and broccoli florets alternately on skewers.
Brush with marinade and grill for about 10 minutes, turning often for even cooking.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spoon into skillet of the heated oil.
Fry patties 2 minutes (or until golden brown).
Turn and fry other side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mystery pie
directions: Crush crackers, mix in nuts and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into cracker mixture and pour into greased pie plate and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Eat and enjoy!

title: potato-mushroom bake
directions: In a buttered shallow baking dish, layer potatoes, onion and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with salt, black pepper and tarragon.
Pour in cream.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil.
Continue baking for 30 minutes longer or until potatoes are fork tender, sauce has thickened and is creamy and smooth. Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix egg, milk and melted shortening (cooled).
Add to flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten flour mixture.
Do not beat.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Serve with butter, syrup, honey or jelly.

title: jello salad
directions: When jello is partially set, add pineapple.
Let set.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Add sugar, cornstarch and eggs.
Cook until thick and add vanilla.
Cool. After cooled, place on top of set jello.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Place on top of sauce mixture.
Top with Cool Whip, shredded cheese and nuts.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place squash and onions
in
colander and add salt; let stand for 2 hours.
Boil
vinegar
and add sugar.
Boil for 10 minutes. Combine squash, onions, mustard seed and celery seed with
sugar and
vinegar
solution and simmer for 10 minutes. Seal in sterilized jars.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Blend all dry ingredients. Add 2 cups milk. Blend; measure out another 1/2 cup milk and add until mixture is moist, NOT too wet.
Dump into greased and floured 10-inch iron skillet. Make an X on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. While warm, rub stick of butter over top and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of sugar.

title: creamed turkey soup
directions: Cook until tender the butter or oleo and onion.
Add and cook for 20 minutes the chicken broth and diced potatoes.
Add and cook for 10 minutes the cubed turkey, peas, carrots, salt and pepper and rubbed sage.
Stir in and heat until hot the cream and milk.
Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cook onion in butter or margarine until softened.
Add cabbage and vinegar.
Cook gently, covered, until cabbage is crisp-tender, about 12 minutes.
Add sugar, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Cook gently 5 minutes longer, stirring often to prevent burning.

title: brownies
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top of pie.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until set.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; set aside.
Mix together and put in bottom of cake pan the rhubarb or sour cherries, brown sugar and melted butter.
Put the batter on top.
Bake.
Eat with milk while warm, or cold is good, too.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix well and let set 2 to 3 hours.

title: white lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef, onions, celery and garlic.
Stir in basil, oregano, salt and dash of pepper.
Add cream and cream cheese. Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir in wine.
Gradually add Gouda and Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: fruit medley salad
directions: In large bowl, combine pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, red apple, strawberries, seedless red grapes and kiwi fruit.
Then cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, fold in the blueberries, cherries and the bananas.
GENTLY TOSS.
ENJOY.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, and put into a 9 X 13-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme until well blended.
Serve with fruit.

title: best salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Remove bones and skin from salmon. Flake meat.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add reserved liquid, 1/3 cup crumbs, eggs, mustard and salmon.
Mix well. Shape into patties.
Roll in remaining crumbs. Fry in
a small amount of oil until nicely browned.

title: cherry oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with Crisco.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat on medium until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop tablespoons of dough 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cook 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hot potato salad
directions: In remaining bacon grease, brown onion.
Add flour and mix well.
Add white vinegar and water.
Cook until thickens.
Pour over the potatoes which have been sliced thin in casserole. Sprinkle broken bacon over top and cook in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: granola
directions: Hold out wheat germ until after baking.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add buttermilk, soda in buttermilk and flour.
Beat well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Crumb Mixture.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together butter, evaporated milk, cheese soup, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook spinach as per directions on package.
Use paper towel to blot after draining.
Cook noodles as per directions on package.
Grease baking dish.
Add noodles and spinach to mixture. Top with cheese.
Cover and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a medium bowl using wire whisk until smooth. Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Press strawberry halves into cream cheese layer, reserve several for garnish.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Season to taste.
Drain off grease; set aside.
Mix flour, eggs and enough milk to make a very sticky dough (a dough similar to the dough you make for dumplings).
Bring water to boil; cut dough into boiling water. Cook until dough comes to the top.
Drain.
Add to hamburger and onion.
Add enough milk to almost cover the dough and hamburger, then heat until milk starts to a boil.

title: potato nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and mashed potatoes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to the butter mixture, alternating with milk. Separate eggs and reserve the yolks for the frosting.
Whip the whites until fluffy, forming peaks.
Fold the whites into the batter last.
Pour batter into 2 prepared layer cake pans and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: pork chops
directions: On each chop, put 1 tablespoon raw rice, 1 slice onion, 1 ring bell pepper and 1 tomato (out of can).
Into tomato juice, add Worcestershire sauce, 2 shakes Tabasco sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Blend all ingredients; drop mixture by spoonfuls into hot oil (375°).
They will brown in about 1 minute.
Drain and serve with tartar sauce.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Heat together soup, Cheez Whiz, chili powder and garlic powder and pour over hominy and onion in baking dish (9 x 13-inch). Crunch Fritos and sprinkle on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients, except marshmallows.
Mix well. Spoon into buttered casserole.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Dump first 6 ingredients into bowl. Add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Mix thoroughly. Divide and shape into logs. Roll in chopped pecans.
Best when made the day before serving. Makes 2 large or 4 small logs.

title: mexican style black-eyed peas
directions: Soak and cook black-eyed peas in water according to package directions; drain.
Cook bacon with onion and garlic in large soup pot over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until bacon is lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Add cooked peas and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce to low heat. Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
9 side dish servings.

title: red and green apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except walnuts.
Refrigerate.
Sprinkle with walnuts, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dahreush's cookie cake
directions: Cook first four ingredients over slow fire or in a double boiler until thick as a custard.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan over a low fire; stir in the sugar. Remove from fire and cool. Beat eggs; beat into butter/sugar mixture. Add vanilla.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In 12 qt. Dutch oven over medium heat in hot salad oil, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring frequently, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
reduce heat to medium-low, partially cover, and cook 2 hours.
Makes 10 pints.
Freeze in bags or boxes.
Each pint is enough to serve over 8 oz. pkg. spaghetti.

title: never-fail pickles
directions: Sterilize 2 pint jars and pack with well scrubbed cukes that have been sliced in half lengthwise.
Tuck a sprig of dill and half clove of garlic.
Mix water, vinegar and salt and bring to boil.
Pour hot liquid in and seal securely.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cut each biscuit into quarters, placing a few at a time in a plastic bag filled with sugar and cinnamon, shake to coat.
After coating all pieces, place them in a greased Bundt or tube pan.
Layer as you go with raisins and/or nuts.
Melt butter and add brown sugar; pour over the biscuits.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: fudgy peanut butter bars
directions: Combine flour, peanuts, brown sugar and butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press onto bottom of pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown around edges.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Sift together next 5 ingredients. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
(This will be quite stiff so mix by hand.).
Add chopped ingredients.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Mix until blended.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Press each ball around a Kiss. Bake 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Set oven to 350°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs until creamy.
Mix in flour, oatmeal, soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for ten to twelve minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients; add oil and mix as you would pie crust. Mix together the remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture. Divide dough in half. Roll between wax paper. Use large cookie sheet (18 x 12). Spread bottom layer with 2 cans of cherry pie filling. Roll top the same as bottom and put over cherry filling. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and cut broccoli; add raisins, sunflower seeds, onion and bacon.
Mix together Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour mixture over broccoli mixture.
Great summer salad!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In hot butter in skillet, saute onion until golden.
Add beef, garlic, flour, salt, pepper, paprika and mushrooms.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Then add soup, simmer, uncovered for about 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Sprinkle with parsley or chives.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute the garlic and onion in oil until clear.
Add eggplant and toss lightly.
Add zucchini and bell pepper and cook 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Remove cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes more.
Serves 6. Can be used hot or cold.
Goes well with barbecue.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: In a 9-inch pie pan, put all the ingredients. Mix with fork until well blended. Work with hands and shape in pan. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chinese rice
directions: Boil or fry chicken breasts until done.
Cut up into small pieces and place in deep frying pan.
Add cream of chicken soup and add add water to right consistency.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until vegetables are done.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6.

title: fruit salad dressing with festive fruits
directions: Dressing:
Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Add lemon and orange juice and rinds.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburg, bread crumbs, cheese, eggs and garlic. Roll into small balls and bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mamow's stack cake
directions: Best to set for 24 hours before serving.
The old folks used dried apples between the layers.

title: cinnamon and chocolate coffee
directions: Put 2 tablespoons chocolate into large cup; add coffee.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar and cream to taste.
Float whipped cream on top; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Can be "spiked" with Irish whiskey.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Put bite-size lettuce
pieces in bottom of bowl.
Layer peas, chestnuts and mushrooms.
Frost with mayonnaise and sour cream, mixed.
Sprinkle with
sugar
and Parmesan.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill
overnight.
Top
with
grated
Cheddar, boiled eggs and bacon before serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice and soup mixture into large baking dish.
Place chicken over top.
Pour 3 tablespoons of melted butter over all. Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 225°.

title: chicken tortilla dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover bottom of pan with some mixture.
Roll mixture in tortillas and spread remaining mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake in 350° oven until warm and cheese is melted.
Picante sauce spooned on top is good.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups. Bring to boil and stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add 1 1/2 cups water, pineapple and blueberries.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: stuffed eggplant(2 main dish servings)
directions: Cut a large horizontal slice from eggplant.
Remove pulp and cut into cubes.
Cook eggplant cubes in a small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain well.
While eggplant is cooking, saute mushrooms, onion, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add well drained eggplant, cream and pimento.
Fill eggplant shell.
Top with 2 tablespoons buttered bread crumbs and 2 slices of bacon which have been crisply cooked and crumbled.
Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Mix beef, salt and pepper and form into 8 patties.
Brown in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients to make a sauce.
Pour over hamburgers.
Simmer 20 minutes or until done.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions and drain.
Mix soups and enchilada sauce together.
Pour over hamburger.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. While hamburger is simmering, crush chips and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour hamburger mixture over chips.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: blushing rose punch
directions: Blend cranberry cocktail, sugar and lemonade well.
Chill just before serving.
Pour mixture over raspberry sherbet.
Stir in ginger ale.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble, brown and drain sausage.
Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 350° until eggs set good, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: delicious pecan pralines
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan combine sugars and cream over medium heat.

Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, to 228° on candy thermometer or until syrup spins a 2-inch thread from spoon. Add pecans, butter and vanilla; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently to 236° or until forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat; stir until slightly thick, but still glossy (200°).
Drop by rounded tablespoon 2 inches apart on a greased pan or waxed paper. If mixture becomes too thick, stir in a small amount of water.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine sugar and egg. Beat well. Add milk and oil and beat. Add bananas. Beat, then add flour. Stir in nuts. Put in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken breasts poached(microwave)
directions: On 2 connected paper towels, place 1/2 cup vegetables.
Top with chicken.
Dot with butter and season.
Fold sides of paper towels over chicken, tucking under ends.
Moisten "package" with sprinkling of water and place on microwave plate.
Cook 1 pack on High (100% power) for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Cook 2 packs for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: hungarian pork chops and potato casserole
directions: Rub pork chops with garlic season, paprika, salt and pepper. Roll in flour and brown in hot oil in skillet.
Remove chops from pan.
Into skillet, add 1 can cream of mushroom soup, milk and sour cream.
Stir and heat slowly until hot.
Set aside.
Place sliced potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with soup mixture. Place browned pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with additional paprika. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with tossed salad and hot rolls.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender; drain.
Arrange in 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend together and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough into pizza pan and bake until lightly golden brown.
Do not overbake.
Spread cream cheese sweetened with powdered sugar on top of cooled cookie crust.
Layer pineapple, bananas, kiwi, mandarin oranges, strawberries and blueberries on top of cream cheese filling.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip. Garnish as desired with extra fruit or nuts.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with unbaked pastry.
Spread rhubarb which has been cut in thin pieces, over pie crust.
Heat milk; add butter.
Beat egg yolks; add sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually pour hot milk into egg mixture.
Pour this custard over the rhubarb.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into quart sized, covered jar.
Refrigerate.
This goes well with almost any kind of dinner.

title: meat loaf parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

title: easy pasta bake
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain. Stir in cooked pasta, spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese. Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: dill garden dip
directions: Mix cottage cheese and lemon juice in blender for 3 to 5 minutes at medium speed until smooth. Stir in onion powder, parsley, dill and pepper.
Chill and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: zucchini nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease standard size muffin pans.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Grease pans (do not flour).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
May double the recipe for 2 loaves.

title: creamy lemon pudding cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix wafer crumbs, 1 Tbsp. sugar and butter; press firmly onto bottom of 9-inch spring form pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Beat cream cheese, remaining 3/4 c. sugar, flour and milk in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until just blended. Add sour cream; beat until just blended. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition until just blended. Stir in dry pudding mixes until just blended. Bake for 1 hour 5 minutes to 1 hour 15 minutes or until center is almost set. Run knife or metal spatula around side of pan to loosen cake; cool completely. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Remove side of pan. Top cheesecake with whipped topping and white chocolate curls, if desired, just before serving. Store leftover cheesecake in refrigerator.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, saute onion in margarine until tender. Reduce heat to medium.
Add milk and cream cheese; stir until cream cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat a heavy, cast-iron skillet or baking dish (well-greased).
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour 1/2 the batter in heated dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together.
Stir eggs, salt, sugar, oil and pineapple together.
Add dry ingredients to carrots, nuts and coconut.
Mix in pineapple mixture, then add vanilla. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour over sugars.
Beat well.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Beat well.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder.
Add cereals, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour sugar mixture over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Let sit 15 or 20 minutes.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove promptly onto cooling rack.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Stir together fudge topping and whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Remove pie from freezer and let sit 5 minutes before cutting.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Measure flour and set aside.
Dissolve yeast into 2/3 cup warm water in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add warm milk, sugar, salt, margarine, eggs and 3 cups flour.
Mix with mixer until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a smooth dough.
Turn onto floured surface.

title: yam 'n apple bake
directions: Peel and slice yams into 1/2-inch slices. Steam in 1 cup water. Don't overcook. Peel and slice apples.

title: moist date bread
directions: Cover dates and raisins with soda and boiling water; set aside.

title: banana chocolate-chip cherry bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda. Mix well and add nuts, maraschino cherries and juice and the chocolate chips.
Place in 1 or 2 pans in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour corn over meat; pour potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: volcano cake
directions: Grease and flour sheet cake pan. Put nuts and coconut on bottom of pan. Mix cake as directed on box. Pour over nuts and coconut. Combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese and butter. Mix until smooth. Drop by spoon on top of cake mix. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and apricot preserves together well.
Then add milk and Cool Whip.
Put in a 9-inch graham cracker crust in pie tin.
Sprinkle ground peanuts on top.
Chill 3 hours.

title: lo mein
directions: Melt margarine.
Brown soup noodles, turning and stirring constantly (about 5 minutes).
Add chicken broth and onion soup. Mix and cover on low heat about 10 to 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and serve.

title: tv snacks
directions: Mix all pretzels, nuts, Chex and Cheerios in a bowl.
Mix all other ingredients in another bowl.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Store in airtight container.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt together Milky Way bars and milk.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk.
Pour in freezer.
Fill remaining part of freezer with milk.
Freeze.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: lemon salad dressing
directions: Place lemon pepper, ground pepper and Mrs. Dash in shaker bottle.
Peel garlic cloves; score them on all sides.
Add olive oil and lemon juice.
Shake well and drizzle over salad.
Tastes best if you make it a few hours ahead.
If stored in refrigerator, bring to room temperature before using.

title: haystack beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding spices to taste.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Spray large dish, line with tortillas.
Brown meat, onion and seasonings, drain and add undrained beans, mix.
Spoon on tortillas; cover with grated cheese.
Place soup and tomatoes in blender, mix well.
Pour soup over casserole.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Make and refrigerate overnight before baking.

title: fast 'n' flameless candy
directions: Pour sugar and corn syrup into frying pan.
Stir to boiling. Add corn flakes and peanut butter.
Stir until syrup mixture covers corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: orange surprise salad
directions: Take the first 3 ingredients and boil and cool completely. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for several hours in a long Pyrex dish.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter. Add Karo. Add sugar gradually (don't get on side of pan). Add salt and nuts.
Turn on high and stir constantly until it
makes a good crackle in water.
Pour out on 2 ungreased cookie sheets.
Put chocolate on top and let melt, then spread.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine milks.
Soak onions in milk mixture.
Dip into flour; shake off excess.
Re-dip into milk and then into flour again; shake.
Fry in deep fat.

title: fruit marlow
directions: Blend marshmallows and milk in saucepan over low heat, folding until marshmallows are almost melted.
Remove from heat and fold until mixture is smooth. Cool. Gradually fold in drained fruit and flavoring.
Fold mixture into whipped cream. Freeze in refrigerator until firm, stirring once during freezing.
Serves 10.

title: portuguese stew
directions: Heat olive oil in large pot.
Lightly brown meat 3 to 6 minutes.
Remove.
Brown onions.
Add mushrooms and lightly brown. Add tomatoes, wine, chicken stock, pepper, salt, parsley and basil (if desired).
Return meat to pot.
Stir after adding each ingredient (fennel also may be desired).
Stir completely.
Simmer 45 minutes, stirring often.
Thicken, if desired, with cornstarch or flour.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning and cook according to package directions.
Layer meat and remaining ingredients.
Serve with Catalina salad dressing.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Heat butter and chocolate in 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan, 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Add Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust and top with cherry pie filling.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Split tomato down sides to middle of tomato.
Mix tuna, salad dressing and relish together in small bowl.
Place mixture in tomato.
Serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of 3-quart covered casserole.
Sprinkle soup mix over rice.
Arrange chicken on top.
Melt oleo in water; pour over chicken and rice.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°, covered, for 1 hour and uncovered 30 minutes.

title: candy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients only until coated with milk.
Press in wax paper-lined loaf pan.
Bake at 250° at least 1 hour.
Chill before slicing.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: * You can substitute crushed oatmeal.

title: sue's cheesecake cookies
directions: Using a muffin tin, place a vanilla wafer on the bottom of a cupcake paper.
Mix eggs, sugar and cream cheese until blended. Fill muffin tin halfway with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool; top with cherry pie filling.

title: finger jello
directions: Pour water into a bowl.
Sprinkle gelatin over the water to soften and dissolve.
Microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes to further dissolve gelatin.
Stir orange juice concentrate into water mixture and pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Chill and cut into fun shapes.
Serve cold or at room temperature.
Serves 16.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When cool add pineapple, bananas, strawberries and nuts.
Pour half of the mixture into mold or dish.
Let congeal.
Spread over this 1 container of sour cream.
Return to refrigerator and chill.
Then pour over the sour cream the rest of the strawberry mixture and congeal.

title: beef roulades
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Add milk and 2 tablespoons melted butter, mixing until smooth.
Let batter stand 2 hours, or refrigerate overnight.
Brush the bottom of a 7-inch crepe pan with melted butter; place pan over medium heat until butter is just hot, but not smoking.
Pour a scant 1/4 cup batter into pan.
Quickly tilt pan in all directions so batter covers the pan in a thin film.
Cook about 1 minute.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Beat eggs, milk, mayo, salt, oregano and pepper.
Add beef mixture and cheese.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until test knife comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter chocolate squares
directions: In a medium bowl, mix peanut butter, butter, sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
(Mixture will be very thick.) Spread evenly into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecued onions
directions: Parboil onions 5 minutes.
Drain and place in a buttered shallow 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Mix catsup, water, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Spread over onions.
Sprinkle mixture with brown sugar and bacon.
Bake uncovered until tender, 30 minutes, at 375°.

title: taco salad
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, place crumbled ground beef and onion.
Microwave on High for 4 to 7 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring 2 to 3 times to break it apart.
Drain, add beans, water and seasoning mix.
Microwave on Medium for 10 to 13 minutes, until the mixture thickens and bubbles, stirring once during cooking time.

title: hot crawfish dip
directions: Melt butter.
Add Worcestershire, parsley, shallots and crawfish.
Mix.
Combine with softened cream cheese.
Add milk. Simmer until warm.
Add seasoning to taste.
Serve on melba toast rounds.
Serves 2.

title: steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Fry bacon in a frypan.
Remove.
Brown steak in bacon grease. Remove.
Put can of mushroom soup, water and onion in a small frypan.
Heat.
Place steak in roaster.
Pour gravy over steak. Crumble bacon and parsley over steak and cover.
Bake at 325° for approximately 3 hours.

title: sesame-cheese popcorn
directions: Combine margarine and sesame seed in small saucepan; stir over low heat until sesame seed is lightly browned.
Set aside. Sprinkle cheese sauce mix and salt over popcorn.
Drizzle margarine mixture over popcorn, tossing well to evenly coat popcorn.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Chop all vegetables and lay each on paper towel to drain. Change towel two or three times, making sure there is no liquid left.
Mix all ingredients together in food processor.
Feeds 50 people.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Pull meat off chicken and put in butter baking dish.
Layer with onion, Doritos, cheese and soup mixed with Ro-Tel tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; 1/2 hour covered and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: roasted potatoes with caramelized garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put 2 tablespoons olive oil in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat in oven for 3 to 5 minutes. Add potatoes. Toss to coat. Roast potatoes, turning occasionally, for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
While potatoes are baking, prepare garlic.
In a small skillet, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil. Add the garlic.

Cover pan and cook over very low heat for 5 to 8 minutes until garlic is tender. Sprinkle with sugar and stir until garlic is golden. Add vinegar, wine and basil. Simmer 2 minutes. Spoon over roasted potatoes. Sprinkle with pepper and parsley. Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: slow cooker beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot 4 hours on low (covered), 2 hours on high (uncovered) or 4 hours on high (last 2 hours uncovered).

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together, pour into a casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes (until bubbly).

title: cherry cobbler(peaches or blueberries)
directions: Melt Oleo in bottom of dish.
Mix together, flour, sugar, milk, and baking powder.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in which bars are to be baked.
Spread crumbs over butter (mix and pack).
Sprinkle on chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned at 325°.
Cut into bars.

title: rocky road cake
directions: In a medium saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over 1 cup of milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved (about 5 minutes).
Add chocolate chips and continue cooking, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted.

title: english muffin cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except English muffins.
Spread cheese mixture on muffins.
Broil until cheese is browned.
Serves 6.

title: layered bean dip (pizza)
directions: Mix refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix. Spread on 12-inch round platter.
Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth.
Spread on top of mixture. Spread sour cream on top of avocado mixture.
Top with shredded lettuce, cheese, taco sauce, tomatoes and black olives (will resemble a pizza).

title: meat pot pie
directions: Season steak with salt and pepper.
Dredge steak in flour. Brown steak in melted butter in 10-inch skillet.
Add celery, mushrooms, onion and water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add carrots, peas and browning for gravy.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch (2-quart) baking pan.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Put potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes, until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of the strawberry mixture into a casserole dish.
Cover remainder and keep at room temperature.
Refrigerate portion in casserole dish until set.
Spread with sour cream; let sour cream come to room temperature for easier application.
Top with remainder of strawberry mixture and return to refrigerator.
Allow to congeal completely before serving.
This dish compliments turkey and dressing or ham nicely.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine cornmeal and remaining ingredients.
Stir into corn mixture first ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
A generous 8 servings.

title: yeast bread rolls
directions: Mix yeast, salt and 1/4 cup water; stir.
Add sugar, shortening and 2 cups water, then gradually add flour.
Knead and let it rise until double in size.
Now it's ready to shape in rolls or a loaf. Let rise again, then bake at 400° for 20 minutes if making rolls or bake loaf at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Precook broccoli.
Precook rice.
Precook chicken.
Add soup, mix well and sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maple syrup sweet potatoes
directions: Place butter in baking dish; place in oven to melt as oven preheats to 350°.
Prepare potatoes; cut into 2-inch chunks.
Turn potatoes in melted butter in baking dish until coated on all sides.
Drizzle syrup evenly over potatoes; sprinkle with sunflower seeds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until heated through.

title: baked beans by patrick
directions: Saute the cup of onions, celery and pepper slightly, then add to pork and beans and corned beef hash; add garlic and barbecue sauce.
Place mixture in baking dish and stripe with bacon slices. Bake in 325° oven for approximately 1 hour or until bacon is cooked.
May cover with foil for first 30 minutes, then uncover so bacon may brown.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then add the rest.
Flour and oil the pan.
Put in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour; test.
If not done, cook 15 minutes more.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; refrigerate 1 hour.
Chop the eggs fine and refrigerate 1 hour.
Add the celery, onion and tuna and refrigerate 1 hour.
Add relish, mustard and Miracle Whip to taste.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat with mixer until well mixed.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clam casserole
directions: Put in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes. Feeds about 6 to 8 people.

title: pickled watermelon rind
directions: Cut rind into 1-inch cubes; trim off outer green skin and bright pink flesh.
Soak overnight in enough salted water to cover; drain.
Heat sugar and vinegar to boiling.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag.
Add spice bag and melon rind to vinegar mixture. Cook, uncovered, until melon is transparent, about 45 minutes. Discard spice bag.
If desired, add a few drops of red or green food coloring to the rind.
Pack watermelon rind tightly into hot, sterilized jars.
Pour boiling syrup over watermelon to within 3/8-inch from top, making sure vinegar solution covers rind.
Seal each jar at once.
Makes 3 pints.

title: chicken biscuit pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir soup and water together slowly; heat. Blend in chicken, peas and pimentos.
Place in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with biscuits.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma bollinger's friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Add to a cup of water (hot) to suit taste.

title: cake with a surprise
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour 1/2 in cake pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Melt caramels with Eagle Brand in double boiler; spread on cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans on top.
Use rest of cake mix.
Bake until done.

title: fruit pancakes
directions: Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients. Do not mix too well. Leave slightly lumpy.
Makes 10 to 15 pancakes.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp. Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add raw shrimp and marinate several hours or overnight. Grill the shrimp on skewers until they turn pink and are firm.
Allow approximately 5 to 8 large shrimp per person.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Mix jello, water, juice and sugar.
Add fruit.
Chill until partly set; blend in whipped cream and pour into flat dish.

title: coconut honey bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Spread or press into a well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares. Makes 24 bars.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Brown together, then drain the first 4 ingredients.
In a large kettle (4 to 6-quart), add beans.
Combine vinegar, sugar, ketchup and tomato juice.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
You can also bake this in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mock sour cream raisin pie
directions: In pan, combine milk and yogurt.
Add pudding.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in allspice. Add raisins and mix well.
Let cool 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into pastry shell.
Chill at least 2 hours. Serve with whipped topping.

title: potato skin appetizers(serve immediately.  makes as many as needed.)
directions: Bake potatoes; cut them into thick strips and slice off top layer of potato.
Mix together cooked crumbled bacon, spring onions, cheese, garlic salt and sour cream.
Butter potato strips and add sour cream mixture.
Reserve some bacon to put on top. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: snow bears(drink)
directions: Place all in blender and liquefy.
Pour into high-ball glass.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Makes 1 (10-inch) tube cake.
Cream butter, oleo and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with each addition.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

title: caraway-cucumber slaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix well oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Stir in sour cream and caraway seed.
Add cabbage and cucumber; toss to mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: happy day cake
directions: Mix together well dry ingredients and then liquids.
Add the milk slowly and blend until smooth with mixer.
Makes two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: more casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions until brown; drain.
Salt meat to taste. Cook noodles until tender.
Mix meat, onion and noodles and place in buttered baking dish.
Mix cheese with remaining ingredients. Bake in moderately heated oven for 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar, eggs (one at a time).
Mash bananas.
Add bananas, soda, and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Bake in a loaf pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour into 9 x 12-inch pan. Add 1/2 package hash browns.

title: mom's beef stew
directions: Brown meat on
all
sides.
Reduce
heat and add onions and garlic.
Cook
until
onions
are soft but not brown.
Add tomato sauce, water,
peppercorns, bay leaf, bouillon cube and chopped parsley.
Simmer on low heat 1 hour.
Add the wine and simmer until meat	is
tender.
Prepare
potatoes and carrots. Cook in a separate pot until just tender.
Add salt as desired while cooking.
Use
as
little water as possible.
Add to the meat, water and
all.
Best refrigerated overnight and reheated.

title: no steak window cleaner
directions: Mix all together in spray bottle.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix salt, sugar and cornstarch and add vinegar.
Heat in the top of a double boiler over direct heat, stirring constantly. When mixture boils, place it over hot water and cook, stirring often for 5 minutes.
Add beets, stir and cover.
Let heat over hot water for at least 30 minutes.
Add butter and serve.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Mix jelly,
ketchup and lemon juice in a crock-pot. Add cocktail sausages.	Cook
about 4 hours.
Remove sausages from juice. Serve
alone
on
toothpicks
or
add
cubed cheese and olives.
Juice may be used as a dip for sausages.

title: baked pork loin
directions: Rub pork with onion that has been quartered.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put fat side up and put onion quarters on top!
Bake at 350° until done.
Very good!

title: adam's mixed-up cereal cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in milk.
Beat eggs and sugars.
Add vanilla, milk mixture and shortening.
Combine with flour and salt.
Add cereal and chips mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Soak hot water and poppy seed for 10 minutes. Combine rest of ingredients and mix well.
Add poppy seed mixture to batter.
Mix and pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and add poppy seed.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet 'n creamy fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, whipped topping and Marshmallow Creme; mix well.
Stir in food coloring.
Spoon into serving dish.
Serve with fresh fruit, vanilla wafers or graham crackers.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: pecan pumpkin pie(my favorite pumpkin pie recipe)
directions: Prepare pie shells and put in 9-inch pie pans.
Cream butter with the 2/3 cup brown sugar in small bowl.
Stir in pecans. Press over bottom of prepared shells in an even layer.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes; remove and cool.
Turn heat down to 350°.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix together and put in jars. Water bath for 20 minutes.

title: the stuff with the rice
directions: In heavy pot, saute chopped onion and pepper in one tablespoon oil.
When softened a bit, add one can corned beef.
Break up beef and stir until softened.
Add tomato sauce, 1 1/2 cans water, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook for one hour on low heat. Serve over cooked rice with a salad.

title: cherry yum yums
directions: Cream together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: dilled green beans(prepare at least 24 hours before serving)
directions: Drain beans.
Stir all other ingredients together.
Pour over green beans.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours or 2 or 3 days ahead.
If a little soupy, drain a little before serving.

title: kerosene cucumbers
directions: Wash and
dry
enough
cucumbers
for six 1-quart jars. Place a portion of dill in bottom of each jar, 1 hot pepper, 1 clove of garlic, 1 slice onion, 1 teaspoon of whole spices, a small lump of
alum
and
cucumbers.
In
a saucepan, combine vinegar, water and
salt.
Allow
mixture
to come to a boil, then pour into the jars and seal immediately.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs; add milk and flavoring.
Mix well and add coconut, mixing well with all ingredients.
Pour into 2 well-greased pie pans and bake at 350°, until golden brown.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Combine milk, butter, eggs, sugar, biscuit mix, pumpkin and pie spice to taste in blender. Blend until mixed. Turn into greased 9 inch pie pan and bake at 400 degrees for 25 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and rim comes out clean. Cool. Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat bananas; add sugar, eggs and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking soda; mix.
Add oil.
Bake 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water for 3 seconds.
Melt margarine. Beat eggs; add margarine and sugar.
Mix well.
Add vinegar, coconut, pecans and drained raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. baldwin's green tomato relish
directions: Cut up tomatoes, pepper and onion.
Put into pan.
Pour 1/2 cup salt and garlic in pan.
Cover in water and stir.
Soak 30 minutes.
Mix vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Then drain and wash tomato mixture to get salt off.
Put mixture into vinegar and sugar and simmer about 10 or 15 minutes.
Seal.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add vanilla and egg yolks.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture with milk, mixing well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: creamy baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Stir in soy sauce, water and soup.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: texas tortilla bake
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Drain, stir in tomatoes, enchilada sauce, sliced cheese spread, cumin, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts, set aside.

title: cheesecake brownie cupcakes
directions: Beat Until Smooth and Creamy.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Simmer for about 45 minutes in pot or simmer 4 hours in a crock-pot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar, seasonings and green pepper.
Beat eggs until light; add to corn mixture.
Add milk slowly and stir together.
Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole as you preheat oven to 350°.
Tilt casserole to coat sides with butter.
Slowly stir corn mixture into butter and casserole.
Place casserole in a shallow pan of warm water.
Bake 1 hour or until firm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and 2 tablespoons water in saucepan. Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Stir in half the chocolate chips and vanilla.
Pour into large bowl.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in combined dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips and pecans. Spread in 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies test done.
Cool completely before cutting into squares.
Yields 16 servings.

title: can opener salad
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate to set.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and celery in butter. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings and simmer for about 40 minutes.
Add cooked shrimp just before serving.
Serve over cooked rice. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy chicken enchilada
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; mix well.
Fry tortillas, one at a time, in 2 Tbsp. oil for 5 seconds on each side.
Place a heaping 1/2 cup of chicken mixture on each tortilla.
Roll up each tortilla, place seam side down in a 13x9x2 baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Longhorn cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
When serving, sprinkle chopped lettuce and tomatoes over it.

title: golden spinach squares
directions: Add onions to spinach and cook according to directions.
Drain well.
Mix in cheese, rice, eggs and pepper.
Pour into a well-greased 10 x 6-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender, but still crispy, about 15 minutes. Drain and cool carrots.
Then add onion and pepper, sliced in strips, over carrots.
Cover with marinade.

title: winter take-along casserole
directions: Cook asparagus as directed on package.
In a large skillet, cook onion in butter until tender (not brown).
Stir in flour. Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mix in salt, pepper, eggs and asparagus.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat milk and just before it boils, have the other ingredients ready and add slowly.
When thick pour in crust and add meringue.

title: hungee gungee(stick to your ribs!)
directions: In pressure cooker, layer onions, potatoes, carrots, and meatballs.
Mix soup, water, salt and pepper and pour over layers. Cook for 10 minutes on low pressure.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Cream sugars, oil and eggs.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, and mix well. Add vanilla, bananas and nuts; mix well.
Pour half of mixture into each pan and bake for 1 hour or until brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender; drain.
Mix carrots with onions and green pepper.
Heat the remaining ingredients until completely blended.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple pizza
directions: Lightly spray a 12-inch pizza pan with nonstick spray.
Cut cookie dough as cookies.
Lay circles on pan overlapping.
Use fingers to press dough together to form crust.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes and cool.

title: dietetic bran muffins
