directions: Mix All-Bran and milk.
Add egg and oil and beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to first mixture. Add honey and stir until combined.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes (approximately).

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in heavy skillet; add water, soup mix, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Do not let boil, just simmer.
Combine flour with sour cream and add to meat mixture to heat through.
Serve over steaming hot rice or buttered egg noodles.

title: pecan pie
directions: Set oven to 450°.
Mix butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vigorously eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake on center shelf of oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat to slow (325°) and bake about 30 minutes longer or until knife is clean after inserting in center of pie.
Turn off oven and allow pie to cool on oven shelf.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Pour chicken pieces on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese, then dry dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: buttermilk biscuit sausage pinwheels
directions: With a pastry blender, cut shortening into flour.
Add buttermilk.
Mix on lightly floured board; knead for a few seconds, adding additional flour if necessary.
Roll out onto a lightly floured board into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Carefully pick all shells from crab meat without disturbing lumps.
Break the bread into small pieces and moisten with milk. Mix ingredients being careful not to break the lumps of crab meat. Shape into cakes.
Fry in small amount of butter or broil until medium brown.
Serve hot with crackers or rye bread and quartered lemon (to season).

title: ye old chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: monster dough(feed on tuesdays and fridays)
directions: Do not use for 24 hours after feeding.

title: nutty peach bake
directions: Drain peaches and line bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches, then pour peach juice and melted butter over dry cake mix.
Add chopped nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: batter for deep frying(to coat 12 to 15 fish pieces)
directions: Sift flour into bowl and season with salt and pepper.
Make well in center.
Add the oil and gradually whisk in liquid, working from center outward.
(Whisk until batter is smooth; don't overwork.)
Let batter set about 1 hour at room temperature.
Beat egg whites to form soft peaks and fold gently into the batter just before using.
Consistency of batter may be varied by more or less liquid added.
Thin batter will cook crisper and lighter but some may be lost in oil during cooking.
Thicker batter clings better but tends to be breaky.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes and remove.
Sift powdered sugar over top when cooled.

title: baked minestrone soup
directions: In large ovenproof pot, mix beef, onion, garlic, salt and pepper; add oil and stir to coat.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until meat is browned, stirring occasionally.
Turn oven to 350°; add broth, water, tomatoes, beans, carrots and seasonings; mix well and layer zucchini on top.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
When soup is finished, add cooked pasta. If soup is too thick, thin with more beef broth.
To serve, ladle soup into bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in sugar.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop a teaspoon of mixture for each cookie on shiny side of foil placed on a cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Turn off heat.
Put cookies in oven and take out the next morning.
If not left overnight, leave in oven for 4 to 5 hours.

title: dunk salad
directions: Mix jello and Cool Whip until mixed.
Add milk, pecans and pie filling.

title: italian dish
directions: In a skillet, brown beef with onion, garlic and seasoning. Stir to separate meat. Add
tomatoes and soup. Add all ingredients to cooked noodles in a casserole. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 7-layer tossed salad
directions: Layer ingredients except the cheese in the order shown in a bowl large enough to toss ingredients later.
Spread with mayonnaise and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight and before serving, sprinkle with cheese.
Toss just before serving.

title: apple glazed carrots
directions: Combine carrots, butter, brown sugar and applesauce.
Heat and serve or place in baking dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: grilled corn-on-the-cob
directions: You will also need 8-inch long pieces of foil.

title: marshmallow drops
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in sugar. Remove from heat.
Add eggs.
Return to heat; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; let stand 25 minutes at room temperature, stirring once or twice.
Stir in vanilla and graham cracker crumbs.
Blend in marshmallows, nuts and coconut.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy bar over low heat.
Once melted, mix with Cool Whip, using an electric mixer.
Pour into pie shell.
Place in freezer for a few minutes until firm.
Slice and serve.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sure-jell punch
directions: Pour the hot water over Sure-Jell.
When cool, add tea, juice and ginger ale.
Sweeten to taste.
Serve over ice.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Put the tomatoes and kidney beans into a large soup pot to simmer.
Fry out diced salt pork; remove from grease and discard. Add chopped vegetables and ground round and brown, turning to prevent burning as onions burn easily.
When nicely browned and done, add to soup pot with tomatoes and beans; salt to taste (go easy).
Add generous amount of black pepper.

title: hot stone fence
directions: In a large kettle, pour in apple juice.
Add cloves and cinnamon stick.
Bring to gentle, rolling boil.

title: walnut chicken
directions: In a large skillet, blend broth, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce and sherry.
Add celery.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Reduce heat and simmer covered until celery is tender-crisp about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken and walnuts. Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and put into microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Stir, bring to a boil and boil for 3 additional minutes.
Take out and add soda; stir.
Pour over popcorn in bag. Roll bag closed and place in microwave for 1 minute; take out and shake.
Return to microwave for 30 seconds, take out, shake well and put onto buttered pan to cool.
Break apart and store in airtight container.

title: dilled shrimp dip
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese.
Stir in shrimp, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and dill.
Cover.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: date bars
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Put half of mixture into large (8 x 13-inch) baking dish.
Spread on filling and top with remaining oatmeal.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix together the pudding and milk. Add Cool Whip. Place on top of salad.

title: turkey and cornbread casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Stir all ingredients except cornbread mix. Pour into 10-inch casserole dish and level. Prepare cornbread mix according to directions on package. Pour over turkey mixture. Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). In a medium, nonstick skillet over medium heat, cook chicken until no longer pink and juices run clear. Drain excess fat. Cube the chicken and return it to the skillet. Add the onion, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, parsley, oregano and ground black pepper. Heat until cheese melts. Stir in salt, tomato sauce, water, chili powder, green pepper and garlic. Roll even amounts of the mixture in the tortillas. Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with taco sauce and 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese. Bake, uncovered, in the preheated oven 20 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x9 x 2-inches.
Mix sugars, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla. Beat in water and egg.
Mix in flour.
Stir in peanuts and candies.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake in light brown, 22 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 36 bars.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, egg, bread and sage.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Brown on all sides.
Pour off drippings.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in glass baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter and layer pineapple.
Place cherries in between all pineapple spaces.
Prepare yellow cake mix according to directions or can use white cake mix.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake in 350 degree oven approximately 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain. Add 1 stick of butter.
When melted add Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup and rice.
Mix and pour in casserole dish.
Top with crackers or potato chips, crumbled.
Cook at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: zwieback
directions: Mix
all these ingredients well except pecans and anise seed, and let rise like bread.
When dough is risen, place it on a floured
board
and
work
in the 4 cups of pecans, with flour sprinkled
over
them, and add 3 tablespoons of crushed anise seed.
Cut
dough
so as to make about 6 to 8 flat round or oval loaves about one inch thick.
Place on greased pan and let
rise again to double its size.
Before placing into oven of
375° spread
the dough loaves with beaten egg and bake in hot
oven. Let
loaves cool and cut the loaves 1/4 inch thick slices and roll in sugar and cinnamon that was mixed in a bowl and place
slices on a jelly roll pan and toast in oven until almost dry.

title: beef and cheese pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and part of cheeses and mix.
Spray pie plate with Pam and put mixture in.
Top with remaining cheese.
Make crust over top with rolls, overlapping edges.
Brush raw egg over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: pepperoni pinwheel crescents
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Place 8 pepperoni slices on each rectangle.
Sprinkle each with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Starting at shortest side, tightly roll up each rectangle; pinch to seal.
Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Pinch dough together on one side of each slice to seal.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve with warm sauce, if desired.
Yields 16 servings.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in bowl; mix well.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping.
Add baking powder, soda and cinnamon to remaining mixture.
Stir in egg and milk; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; serve warm. Yields 9 servings.

title: lime punch
directions: Put Sprite in just before serving.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Combine jello and water.
Add cranberry mixture to this mixture and let thicken. Add crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan and set overnight.

title: grilled wrapped franks
directions: Pat frankfurters dry.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Divide dough into 10 equal parts.
Pat 1 part dough around each frank with fingers floured with baking mix, completely covering frankfurter.
(At this point, franks can be covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours.) Preheat oven and bake uncovered on greased cookie sheet until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes, at 450°.

title: zultz
directions: Boil
pork hocks with onion, bay leaves and celery salt.
Cook slowly for 2 hours or so.
Take hocks out of juice.
Pour juice into large bowl.
Cool until fat hardens on the top and then discard all the fat.
While pork hocks are still hot, cut up (removing all fat between skin and meat).
Discard this fat also. To every 4 cups of diced meat, skin, etc., add 3 cups of juice, pepper, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring and tasting.
Pour into pans.
Remove bay leaves and cool.

title: puerto rico chicken
directions: Wash chicken and cut into desired size pieces.
Skinning is optional.
Line baking dish with foil.
Place onion slices in bottom of dish.
Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Place chicken on top of onion slices.
Dot all of floured chicken with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over chicken. Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 300° for one hour.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Mix chili, tomato sauce and hamburger in a bowl.
Pour the mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cornbread as directed, then pour over the chili mixture.
Bake at 350° until cornbread is light brown.
Spread cornbread out over the chili.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons of butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Shake pan to get butter coated with sugar.
Cream remaining butter; gradually add remaining sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and almond extract and mix well. Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating until well blended.
Coat peaches with remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Fold peaches into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, celery and onion.
Mix lightly. Chill.

title: apricot bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 15 square graham crackers.
Melt oleo; stir in sugar, milk and beaten egg.
Cook 5 minutes, until slightly thick.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, coconut, nuts, apricots and vanilla extract.
Spread over crackers and top with another layer of graham crackers (15 squares).

title: tigua hot chili
directions: Brown beef and onion in 3 tablespoons of the shortening; remove from heat.
In a deep saucepan over low heat, melt remaining lard or shortening.
Whisk in flour, stirring until well blended.
Gradually add chili and bouillon in small, alternating amounts, creating a smooth, thick sauce.
Add remaining seasonings, adjusting to taste.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add browned beef and onion.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes.
Degrease the top of the chili, if necessary.
Add potatoes, if desired.
Simmer 20 minutes more.
Meat should be very tender.
If not, simmer another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: noah's ark clam chowder
directions: Simmer 6 hours on low in crock-pot or lowest heat on the stove burner.
Stir occasionally.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Prepare the Rice-A-Roni as directed on package; mix with other ingredients.
Serve over lettuce with tomato wedges.

title: bakery icing(birthday cake icing)
directions: Beat 25 minutes until very smooth and color as you like. Unused portions may be frozen.

title: irma brown's cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and salad oil.
Add eggs, flour, soda and vanilla.
Batter will be fairly stiff.
Pinch batter big cookie size and mash and shape.
Place in baking pan and bake at 350° until done, about 7 minutes on bottom rack and 7 minutes on top rack.

title: uncle bernie's kielbasa casserole
directions: Brown kielbasa for 2 to 3 minutes on each side, then boil for 20 minutes.
Drain sauerkraut.
In a large pot, add 2 to 3 cups of water, whole potatoes, diced onions, 2 to 3 tablespoons of sugar, grated apples, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 45 minutes.
Drain.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
Slice kielbasa into bite size pieces.
Assemble into a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a medium-size bowl.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: gingered plum crisp
directions: *If using fresh ginger, chop fine, mix with 1/4 cup sugar and let sit an hour before using.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Mix and serve on hamburgers.

title: pizza quick casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off excess fat.
Stir in sauce.
Place in bottom of greased long glass baking dish.
Arrange slices of pepperoni on top of hamburger, if desired.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on top.
Mix up Bisquick, milk and egg smoothly.
Pour on top of cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones and spread in a 10 x 13-inch pan. Top with the milk, celery and chicken soup that have been heated together.
Mix dressing, broth and melted margarine; spread on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If cold, bake for 45 minutes. Can be frozen.

title: caramels
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Place on burner and stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring until syrup spins a brittle thread.
Lower heat and add butter.
Stir until melted.
Add slowly and stir evaporated milk.
Increase heat; stir and cook until a small amount forms a firm ball in ice water.
Remove from burner.
Add pecans and salt and pour into buttered 7 x 11-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut and shape into 1-inch squares.
Wrap each square in wax paper.
Yield: about 100 caramels.

title: honey bowl
directions: Bring to a boil the honey, fruit, liquid, cinnamon sticks and oranges.
Simmer for about 1/2 hour; let cool.
Arrange fruits, except for pineapple, inside bottom and sides of glass bowl.
Put pineapple in center.
Pour brandy or sweet vermouth over fruit and let stand.
Mix coconut with boiled honey mixture and pour over fruit.
This should cover the fruit fairly well.
Let stand at least 6 hours, 24 hours or overnight is better, before serving.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs that have been beaten well.
Add sweet potatoes; mix well.
Sift together remainder of dry ingredients, then add alternately with milk and nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add broccoli and cook until tender. Add mushroom soup, cheese, m.s.g., mushrooms and 3/4 cup almonds. Pour in casserole. Sprinkle rest of almonds and bread crumbs on top.
Bake in a 300° oven until bubbly. Serves 18 or more.
This may be made ahead and baked when ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, mix the first 7 ingredients (butter through molasses). When thoroughly mixed, add 4 ripe bananas (cutting them into small pieces helps in mixing). Slowly add 1 1/2 cups flour, pecans and raisins. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°. Check with toothpick for doneness in case additional time is needed. Let cool in pan for 15 minutes or so before removing.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes. Soak in water with 2 tablespoons lemon juice for 1 hour. Then saute onions and carrots in butter. Add potatoes, cream of chicken soup, 6 cans of water, chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste and 1 bay leaf. Simmer. When potatoes are done, add heavy cream and flour (may be lumpy but will melt as it cooks). Add sour cream before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into Pyrex baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients twice; add everything but cheese.
Pour half of batter into greased pan or skillet; sprinkle half cheese on top.
Add remaining batter and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: pat's crunch
directions: Melt almond bark and pour over the combined dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Mash bananas. Add lemon juice and buttermilk. Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually. Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with banana mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake 28 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: dilled zucchini
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter and oil together.
Add zucchini and saute for 1 minute over medium heat.
Add broth and dill; stir to combine.
Cover pot and cook over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until zucchini is cooked, but still crunchy.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cut up boiled egg white into mixing bowl (throw away yolk). Open 2 cans of tuna and drain off water.
Add to bowl and stir. Add lemon juice, sweet salad cubes, mustard and mayonnaise. Sprinkle in minced onion.
Mix together.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Saute the onions in the chicken fat until golden brown.
Add the chicken, paprika and 1 tablespoon of salt.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
During the simmering, stir twice and add a little water if needed.
Add the green pepper, tomato, tomato paste and 1 cup water.
Cover the skillet and cook over low heat for about 50 minutes, stirring and adding a little water as needed to prevent sticking.
Add additional salt to taste.
Serve with rice, noodles or dumplings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini and chopped onions in salted water for 4 minutes.
Mix
together grated carrots, cream of mushroom or chicken soup and
sour
cream.
Melt
margarine
and pour over Pepperidge Farm crumbs.
Put 1/2 crumb mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour
in
vegetables and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Pour on soup mixed with water.
Place raw chicken over soup mixture.
Mix dry soup mix very well; sprinkle evenly over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Remove foil toward the end.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables; combine with celery, green peppers and onion.
Bring last 4 ingredients to a boil; pour over vegetables and chill.
Chill overnight.

title: mandarin mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add juice; allow to cool to room temperature.
Fold in sherbet and vanilla. Refrigerate until partially set.
Fold in oranges; pour into mold. Allow to set overnight.
This is very good made in a ring mold and the center filled with chicken salad.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheese grits
directions: Fix grits in boiling water with salt.
Add margarine and garlic cheese.
Mix eggs in measuring cup.
Beat well and add milk to make 1 cup.
Mix in cheese-grits mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese crumbs.

title: banbury tarts
directions: Mix raisins, sugar, crumbs, egg yolk, butter, lemon juice, lemon rind, nuts and salt.
Roll pastry into 12 x 12-inch square. Cut into 9 (4-inch) squares.
Spread tiny bit of filling over half of each square.
Moisten edges; fold into triangles and press edges together with fork.
Prick tops.
Bake in a 450° oven until delicately browned, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry cheese pie
directions: Make graham cracker crust.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Whip the cream and fold the two together.
Spread over crust.
Top with blueberry pie filling.

title: modeling "goop"
directions: Stir salt and 2/3 cup water over heat 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cornstarch and cold water.
Stir until smooth. Cook until thick.
Store in plastic bag.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix and pour over carrots.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or beat with a mixer 3 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's crab cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into round cakes.
Either fry in oil or brown in butter.
Let crab cakes chill in refrigerator for several hours before frying.
Can also brown in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: In food processor, process cookies until crumbly.
Mix in butter.
Pat into bottom of 9-inch pie pan.

title: lo-cal yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt until blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Heat 1 cup juice and dissolve jello.
Let set to get thick. Stir in the blueberries.
Let get real thick, but not set.
Fold in Dream Whip (made up); just marble through.
Refrigerate until set.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add garlic, parsley, basil, salt, tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Add eggs, salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together sugar, peanut butter, cream cheese and butter. Whip the cream, adding vanilla.
Fold into peanut butter mixture and pour into crust.
Chill overnight.
Serve with a chocolate topping, if desired.
Will yield 12 small, rich servings.

title: melt in your mouth biscuits
directions: Put Bisquick in large mixing bowl.
With your hands, make a hole in the Bisquick.
Add melted butter and sour cream in the hole.
Knead with your hands.
Sprinkle dry flour on wax paper and roll dough out with your hands to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place in slightly greased pan.
Rub butter on top.
Bake in 400° oven.

title: pasta broccoli("all in one pot")
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add all ingredients, except pasta. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Make sure broccoli is soft.
You can also use cauliflower.

title: dumplings(for stew or ham and cabbage)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Rub in Crisco lightly. Add enough water to make dough hold together.
Drop by tablespoon. Simmer 15 minutes.
Don't raise cover for 15 minutes.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Return to pan and add cheese, cook until cheese is melted and add seasonings and mix well.
Spread on slices of party rye bread.
Freeze.
When ready toss serve heat oven to 225 degrees.
Bake until mixture is warm through.

title: chili cheese log
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, salsa and chili seasoning mix.
Mix until well combined, then shape into a log or ball.
Cover log or ball with pecans, then cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 7 servings.

title: buttermilk hush puppies
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Carefully drop batter by level tablespoonful into deep, hot oil.
Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry 3 minutes or until hush puppies are golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yield: about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: salsa al pesto
directions: Pound the basil leaves with the garlic, nuts and a dash of salt in a mortar.
Pound in the cheese and when it is a thick puree, run in the oil as if you were making mayonnaise.
The sauce should be very thick and creamy.
Serve on fish or pasta.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: watermelon rind pickles(3 days)
directions: Cut the rinds in cubes.
Soak 2 hours in ice water with 1/4 cup of salt. Drain off water and add cold water to cover.
Cook 10 minutes or until tender, not soft.
Drain this water off and add the vinegar and spice.
Pour over the rinds and let set overnight.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Blend well.
Add molasses.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix together alternately with sour milk to mixture.
Refrigerate and bake later.
Either roll or drop by spoon.
Very good.
Freezes well. Different.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir onions and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender.
Add water to reserved mushroom liquid to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into onion mushroom mixture with celery, bean sprouts, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and water; stir into vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Serve over chow mein noodles or rice.
Serves 4.

title: old fashioned cornbread
directions: Put sugar, salt, soda and baking powder in a bowl and add buttermilk.
Stir well, then add cornmeal and flour alternately. Melt shortening in iron skillet and add to mixture.
Sprinkle a little cornmeal in iron skillet.
Heat pan and pour mixture into hot pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: noodle dish
directions: In skillet brown beef, onion, green pepper and salt and pepper.
Cook and drain noodles.
Place half of noodles in baking dish, add half of meat.
Add creamed corn.
Add rest of meat, then noodles.
Spread tomato soup on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: Prepare all ingredients before assembling salad.
Layer lettuce, then peas, red onion, cauliflower, celery and finally green pepper in a large glass salad bowl.
Spread mayonnaise or salad dressing over salad to cover salad completely.
Sprinkle mayonnaise with Parmesan cheese, then sprinkle dry Italian salad dressing mix over.
Sprinkle bacon around edge of bowl.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
At serving time, toss salad well with chilled fork and spoon and serve on chilled salad plates, if possible.

title: perky cranberry punch
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients into a large percolator.
Place brown sugar and remaining ingredients in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle of electric percolator.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven!
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flours and milk alternately, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: eggs with tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan.
Cook garlic with onion for two minutes or until soft.
Add tomatoes, parsley, red pepper and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer over low heat for 20 minutes. Drop eggs into sauce, one at a time, without breaking yolks.
Cook slowly for about three minutes, stirring occasionally, until whites are firm.
Serves six.
Serve hot.

title: breakfast "strata"
directions: First, crumble up and cook sausage in separate skillet.

Spray inside of a large baking dish or pan with Pam or other cooking spray, and layer the ingredients as follows: cover bottom of pan with bread cubes, sprinkle a layer of sausage over bread and sprinkle a layer of cheese over the sausage.
Repeat the 3 layers. Beat together eggs, milk and other ingredients; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over the top of all contents of baking pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in low/moderate oven (325° to 350°) for approximately 1 hour (check often for doneness).
Serve with peach halves.

title: mini cocktail meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
In shallow baking pan, arrange meatballs and bake 18 minutes or until done.
Serve, if desired, with assorted mustards or tomato sauce.
Makes about 4 dozen meatballs.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Soak sour milk and All Bran in a separate mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, molasses, flour, soda and salt alternately with soaked All Bran.
Add raisins.
Pour into well greased tin cans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Makes four 14 oz cans or five 10 oz cans.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan and bake as directed.
Cool.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: To increase recipe, use quantities in parenthesis.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer, uncovered, for three hours, stirring occasionally. Pour in jars and seal.
Yields approximately 21 pints.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over butter in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain, set aside.
Melt cheese, soup and milk in pan together.
Add rice slowly.
Stir in broccoli.
Butter a casserole dish and add this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil cloves for 30 minutes. Remove from water. Add tea bags and steep. Remove tea bags. Add sugar and juice. Reheat and serve.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for about 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Mix good. Add vanilla and pour in 9 x 13-inch greased oblong dish, cut into squares when cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs
slightly; add sugar, syrup, juice and rind. Stir in butter.	Spread pecans over pie shell and pour filling over them.
Bake
approximately	45
minutes
in a 350° oven. Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop and toss the onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Grate and add the cheese.
Add avocado and dressing.
Crunch and add the Doritos.
Brown beef.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and beans.
Cook until dry.
Add to tossed mixture and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: fruit jello
directions: Stir frozen strawberries into jello and hot water.
Add pineapple with juice.
Add nuts.
Fills large mold.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except squash, in large mixing bowl.
Add squash, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° in tube pan or two loaf pans for about an hour.
Can test for doneness with toothpick.

title: chili sauce
directions: Do not cook in aluminum pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Put mixture in roasting pan.
Cook down in oven, stirring occasionally with wooden spoon.
When about half reduced, add 10 chopped, peeled apples.
Finish reducing.
Quickly ladle into hot jars.
Cover with hot lids and rings.
Set aside to cool.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add cooking oil and flour. Add baking powder, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Mix well. Add pineapple, nuts and bananas. Bake in 4 (9-inch) pans at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, until done. Cool and frost.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Heat chicken broth and potatoes to boiling in a medium saucepan over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender. Remove from heat but don't drain. Break potatoes into smaller pieces using a fork or masher. Stir in milk, salt, pepper, thyme and onions. Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add cornstarch and continue heating to reach desired consistency.

title: pasta con spinach e ricotta
directions: Fry the onion in oil until golden brown.
Add spinach to onion and oil; cook on low flame until warm.
Using directions from carton, cook pasta (short and tubular pasta is best for this recipe like ziti, rigatoni, mostaccioli, etc.) and set aside.
Two minutes before pasta is done, add Ricotta to the spinach and stir. Pour spinach mixture over pasta and enjoy!

title: russian tea
directions: Sift together several times. Store in airtight container.

title: fran norton's fruitcake squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 baking pan. Spread nuts in pan. In bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla extract.
Spoon over nuts. Sprinkle cherries and pineapple over batter. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and let cool. Before completely cooled, cut into squares.

title: seasoning salt
directions: Combine all ingredients and use for meats and vegetables.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Mix in butter.
Pat into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy mustard glaze for ham
directions: Combine sugar and fruit juice during the last 30 minutes of baking time for ham.
Makes about 1/2 cup of glaze.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan, then melt marshmallows in with butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mold into balls while still warm. The kids love them.

title: chippy dippy bars
directions: Melt butter to cover bottom of pan.
Arrange other ingredients, except milk, in a 9 x 13-inch pan; don't stir.
Pour milk over top, covering all as evenly as possible.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Cut into squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk and cream for 1/2 hour.
Add sugar and eggs.
Soak raisins in hot water.
Add to mixture and add the vanilla, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Pour in greased dish; pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham fritters
directions: Combine flour and baking powder in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in eggs.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Stir in ham and pineapple.
Spoon 1/4 cupfuls into a small amount of hot oil; brown on both sides.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yields 8 servings.

title: turkey soup
directions: Spread Cream Cheese in bottom of baking dish.
Open one can of Chili, pour over top of cream cheese.
Top with cheese of your choice.

title: blueberry crisp(makes 8 servings)
directions: Combine rice, blueberries and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Coat 8 individual custard cups or 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place rice mixture in cups or baking dish and set aside.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites very firm.
Add to the batter mixture.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: chicken galliano
directions: Pound chicken breast pieces thin.
Spread each of the eight pieces with 2 tablespoons of herbed cheese.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
Dredge in seasoned flour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; cream well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk, then add alternately to creamed mixture with 3 1/2 cups flour.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup flour with dates, candy and nuts.
Add to batter with coconut.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Combine orange juice and powdered sugar; mix well.
Pour over hot cake in pan. Let stand in pan overnight.
Remove from pan.

title: green chili
directions: Brown ground meat with flour and margarine.
Dice onion and add to meat mixture. Cook until onion is tender.
Add garlic, salt and pepper, diced tomatoes, chicken broth and chilies.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add water if chili is too thick.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Roll in a mixture of chili powder and paprika or nuts.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell and bake. When cool, top with meringue made from egg whites.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all together and knead for about 3 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Press down and divide into 3 parts.
Makes 3 loaves.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk gradually.
Add cheese and spices.
Stir until thick.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Stir 5 minutes over medium heat to a soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In skillet cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender (about 10 minutes). Stir in parsley and seasonings. In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese; stir in zucchini and onion. Unroll rolls and form into pie crust, brush dough with mustard and pour in mixture. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes and enjoy.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Peel, clean, cut to size, rinse and cook shrimp.
Rinse and cook scallops with shrimp.
Saute onions and celery in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
If not thick enough, I used cornstarch to thicken rest of the way.
Chop about 2 cups of shrimp and scallops.
Put remaining shrimp, scallops and the crab meat in pot.
Heat to boil.
Serve.
Enjoy!
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Add vanilla.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach salad with chutney dressing
directions: Remove stems from spinach; discard. Wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry with paper towels. Set aside.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven per pan directions.
Puncture hot dogs.
Simmer hot dogs until warm.
Unroll crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet. Place one hot dog on each roll.
Roll up to the triangle.
Bake according to the time indicated on crescent roll can.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: old fashioned sour cuke pickles
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add vinegar.
Use quart or pint jars that have been washed, scalded and wiped dry.
If using jars with rubber, do the same.
Use finger length cukes, washed with cold water and wiped dry.
Pack into jars.
Fill jars with vinegar mixture and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cream together.
Place broccoli in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Place American cheese slices on top, then bread crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake 40 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry honey
directions: Cook
water
and sugar together for seven minutes.
Add crushed berries and
boil five minutes.
Add powdered alum and remove from heat.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook celery and onion until translucent.
Add kidney beans, whole kernel corn, stewed tomatoes, taco seasoning and V-8 or tomato sauce or 1 cup water. Put all in crock-pot and let cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Crush taco chips in bottom of each soup bowl.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, cook potatoes in water to cover until tender. Drain. Combine butter or margarine and parsley.
Pour over the potatoes and toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: deer meatballs in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and brown in skillet.
Then add to sauce.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add unbeaten egg and mix well.
Add rind and juice of lemon.
Then the cheese.
Add flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Shape into balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
When cool, dip in fondant or cooked frosting and roll in colored sugars or nuts.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb into pie crust.
Beat egg yolks, sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg together.
Spread over rhubarb and bake at 350°F for 45 minutes.
Beat egg whites with 6 Tbsp sugar for meringue. Spread on pie and bake until nicely browned.

title: bizcochos(mexican sugar cookies)
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add anise seed, vanilla, and beaten eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt together.
Add to mixture.
Roll out and cut with round cookie cutters.

Either sprinkle cinnamon & sugar before on top of the cut-out cookie dough now or, after baking, you can dunk the baked cookies in a cinnamon & sugar mixture. Bake cookies at 450° for approximately 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
approximately 10 dozen small cookies.

title: layered green salad
directions: Wash lettuce and drain on a towel.
Layer lettuce, celery, bell pepper, onion and peas in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour mayonnaise or salad dressing over top of salad.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, cook bacon in microwave and crumble over top of salad.
Also, spread shredded cheese on top.

title: one dish meat loaf dinner
directions: Mix hamburger, sausage, diced onion, salt, pepper and oats in bowl.
Beat egg and add milk, then pour over mix.
Stir well. Loaf will be thick; place in large pan and bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes. Take loaf from oven and lay out potatoes and carrots around the loaf.
Cover with large can of Campbell's tomato soup and bake 60 more minutes.

title: spicy tomato juice
directions: Note:
Add 1 quart tomato juice for cooking tomatoes down.

title: 15 minute stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from meat and reserve.
Cut meat diagonally across grain in very thin strips.
Heat fat in skillet until you have 3 tablespoons melted fat.
If necessary, add butter.
Remove trimmings.
Brown meat.
Add 2/3 cup water and mushrooms.
Stir in soup mix.
Heat to boiling.

title: the thing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, oleo, egg and pecans (will be stiff).
After mixing, press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over first mixture. Bake 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Other cake mixes work as well.

title: grandma's vegetable soup
directions: Prepare all vegetables.
Cook butter beans and corn until almost done.
Mix all together.
Simmer 2 hours.
Place in sterile jars and seal.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add mustard.
Boil water, chili powder and catsup.
Combine the 2 mixtures and simmer 45 minutes. Place on hamburger buns and enjoy.

title: lime-cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and let melt.
Stir in salt and pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cottage cheese, whipped cream and nuts.
Turn into mold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and flour.
Pour into casserole dish with melted butter.
Add peaches and spread into batter.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 30 to 45 minutes or until done in a 350 degree oven.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Bring beans and water to a boil for 2 minutes, then let soak 1 hour.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrot, potato, uncooked rice, onion, bouillon and seasonings.
Brown beef.
Bring soup to boil.
Add meat; cover and simmer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for several hours before serving.
This can be served in a hollowed out loaf of bread.
The pieces of bread can be used to dip.
Also great with vegetable sticks or crackers.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Mix beef, mushrooms, salt, onion, Worcestershire sauce and milk together.
Shape into six patties.
Wrap bacon slice around each patty; secure with toothpick.
Grill 6 to 8 minutes per side (to desired doneness) over medium flame or coals.
Remove toothpick before serving.

title: pasta con ricotta(macaroni with ricotta)
directions: Cook macaroni about 15 minutes or until tender in 5 quarts of rapidly boiling salted water.
Drain; put back in pot and add butter.
Mix Ricotta with milk in a bowl until smooth.
Pour over hot macaroni; simmer 3 minutes over low flame in covered pot. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve very hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: angel meringues
directions: Beat egg whites until creamy.
Add 2/3 cup sugar gradually. Beat until peaks form, fold in walnuts (optional) and vanilla. Drop by the tablespoon on foil covered cookie sheet, forming a well for filling.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then turn off oven and do not open for at least 8 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 meringues.

title: mandarins in wine & liqueur
directions: Mix all ingredients except liqueur, chill.
Pour liqueur over top right before serving.
Serve in fruit cups.
Serves 2.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water with no seasoning.
Drain and mash with fork.
Add onion, carrot, soup, sour cream, margarine and 1/2 to 3/4 of stuffing.
Place in casserole and sprinkle top with remaining stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: Combine honey and Kitchen Bouquet in a large skillet.
Place over low heat.
Turn chops to coat meat on both sides.
Increase heat to medium, brown chops and remove them.
Add a little apple juice to skillet, stir to loosen bits of meat.
Add yams and apples.
Top with chops.
Pour remaining apple juice and seasonings over chops.
Bring to a boil, cover and cook over low or medium heat until tender, about 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
If necessary, add more apple juice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: light tasty biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with fork until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Add milk and blend lightly with fork only until flour is moistened and dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead lightly 30 seconds and roll 3/4-inch thick. Place on lightly greased pan and brush tops of biscuits with butter.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: bacon and egg brunch
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with day-old bread.
Add Cheddar cheese and then bacon.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Beat well and pour over the pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with mushrooms and bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet; cook until browned.
Spread cubed bread into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; then browned sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and mushroom soup together.
Pour over layered bread and sausage mix.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: tamale and corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: tea tassies
directions: Mix until well blended.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add ingredients in order listed, mixing well.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 300° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put chicken on top of rice mixture and season to taste.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Put sliced almonds on top (optional).

title: clam fritters
directions: Grind clams and drain well.
Mix other ingredients together and add clams.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: apple cake squares
directions: Combine the apples, nuts and raisins and set aside.
Combine the flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, vanilla, eggs and oil. Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven. Cover with a towel for 1 hour and then cut into squares.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda. Pour over popcorn and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: derby salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with taco chips.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Melt cheese and oleo.
Add crab and mushrooms; spoon onto quartered muffins.
Broil until slightly browned.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out rolls on a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Spread mixture of cream cheese, dressing packet and Miracle Whip to top of crust.
Then top with assorted vegetables such as: green onions, broccoli, cauliflower, mango, etc.
Place in refrigerator for about 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat marinade
directions: Cut meat into cubes and marinate at least 24 hours.
Perfect for preparing meat for kabobs.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Spread in bottom of large casserole pan.
Mix in the tomato soup.
Drain green beans; spread on top of meat.
Peel and boil potatoes; mash (milk and butter).
Spread on top of the green beans.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and garlic salt in 2-cup measure.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes; stir.
Reduce power to Medium.
Microwave 5 minutes, stirring once. Mix corn flake crumbs with Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Dip chicken in beaten egg, then in crumb mixture.
Place in 10-inch square microwavable casserole.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at Medium-high (70%) until chicken is tender, 9 to 14 minutes, rearranging after half the cooking time.
Do not turn over.
Pour sauce over chicken, then sprinkle with the Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan.
Microwave at Medium-high until Mozzarella melts and sauce is hot, 2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, Tabasco and lemon juice. Mix well.
Stir in olives, then oysters (carefully).
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: quick pizzas
directions: Spread pizza sauce on cut sides of bun.
Place your chosen meat on each bun (if pepperoni 5 to 6).
Cover with cheese; place on broiler pan.
Broil at middle position for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Sift together flour, pudding
mix
and
baking
powder. Combine egg, milk and melted
margarine;
add
to dry ingredients. Mix well.
Spread
in
a
greased
8 x 8 x 12-inch pan. Drain peaches,
reserving
cup
liquid.
Chop peaches and sprinkle atop batter.
Beat together the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach liquid.
Pour atop peaches.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cottage cheese jello
directions: Sprinkle the package of dry jello over the cottage cheese. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Drain the can of crushed pineapple and mix into cottage cheese mixture.
Serve and eat or may be chilled.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Makes 1 pint.

title: strawberry cream dip
directions: Mix well.
Tastes really great with strawberries and bananas.

title: strawberry crush
directions: In food processor with knife blade attached, blend frozen strawberries until strawberries resemble finely shaved ice, stopping processor occasionally to scrape down sides.
Add yogurt and confectioners sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: hash brown-ham casserole
directions: Mix everything together except oleo, corn flakes and Mozzarella cheese.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix oleo and corn flakes together. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: awesome apples
directions: Combine brown sugar, granola and cinnamon in a medium bowl. Mix well.
Put equal amounts of mixture into each apple.
Put apples in a large baking dish.
Place 1 teaspoon margarine on each apple.
Pour water into baking dish and bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 1 hour.
Add more water if necessary.

title: new year cookies
directions: Mix batter and drop by 1/2 teaspoon into deep fat (oil) until brown.
(Push batter off with your finger.)

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate in butter.
Cool and add rest of ingredients. Mix well and bake in prepared Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Remove cake while hot and place under tight fitting cover until cool.

title: crusty fish fillets
directions: Cut fillet into serving pieces.
Place in a baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 salt and pepper, dry mustard and lemon juice. Pour over fish.
Sprinkle with toast crumbs and parsley flakes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for approx. 45 minutes.

title: good dip(lo-cal)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Good for dip or to add to dressings for potato or cabbage salad.
One envelope Lipton dry vegetable soup mix may be substituted for the Ranch dressing mix.

title: traveling snack
directions: Melt the peanut butter with the butterscotch bits.
Add the noodles and peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by a teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Allow to harden.
This yields 5 dozen pieces.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all but the shrimp in a blender or food processor and blend.
Add the shrimp and process or chop.
Refrigerate.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour in a large baking dish (sprayed).	Top with dots of margarine and about 1/2 cup cornflake crumbs.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Do not overbake.

title: glaze for fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over Fresh Apple Cake.

title: apple (or pear) cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Mix together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture. Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured (or sprayed) 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May be glazed or served with whipped topping.

title: layered chocolate pudding dessert cake
directions: Mix flour or crumbs, nuts and butter or margarine.
Press into 2 or 3-quart baking dish or pan.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: granny's hot chocolate
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/3 cup cocoa mixture with 1 cup of hot water. Add a little more to make a richer taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, raisins, walnuts, bacon and onion.
Set aside.
Make the salad dressing by combining mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour dressing over salad mixture and chill.
Let set for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: stuffed chicken rolls
directions: Place approximately 1 tablespoon prepared stuffing mix in center of each fillet and roll up.
Place in square baking dish sprayed with Pam (glass for microwaving), seam side down.
Repeat with other fillets.
Mix together bread crumbs, parsley flakes and seasoned salt.
Spray top of each fillet with Pam and sprinkle with bread crumb mix.
Microwave at 50% power for 15 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.
Serve with topping of White Sauce.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add chicken, coating well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove chicken; roll in crumbs and arrange in 9 x 13-inch shallow pan.

title: peach parfait
directions: In top of double boiler cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add the slightly beaten egg.
Cook over hot water until coats the stirring spoon.
Cool.
Whip the cream and combine with the custard mixture.
In individual tall dessert glasses or large glass bowl layer the crushed wafers, peaches, ginger and custard cream, ending with custard cream to keep peaches from air.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Cook over low heat, approximately 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water.
Mix well.
Add to blueberry mixture.
Cook until thick.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil, sugar, zucchini, vanilla and honey. Mix well. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add gradually to zucchini mixture. Fold in nuts. Bread can be baked in several containers. Bundtlet pans bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven. Never fill pans more than 1/2 full. Check with toothpick for doneness. Empty tin cans (fill 6 regular size green bean cans 1/2 full) and bake as directed.

title: chicken luau
directions: Remove skin, excess fat and bones from chicken breasts; cut meat into bite size pieces.
In large bowl, combine chicken pieces, pineapple chunks and juice and next 4 ingredients.
Heat in preheated 450° oven for about 45 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and mixture is heated through.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the boiling water.
Add nuts, apples and cranberry mixture.
Pour into mold and let stand in refrigerator for several hours.

title: marinade for meats
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over meat.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake.

title: spanish eggs
directions: Pour in quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with salsa, sour cream, guacamole, tomatoes.
Enjoy.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all and pour into pie shell.
Top with another pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press in a 13-inch pan 1 stick melted oleo and graham cracker crumbs.
Whip together powdered sugar, 1 stick oleo and egg whites.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Layer bananas and pineapple and top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then vanilla, flour and salt.
Mix	well;
add
soda
to buttermilk and stir well. Add to mixture
and
beat	3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Add black walnuts, if desired.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, melted butter or oleo and buttermilk.
Stir in flour and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until set.

title: coconut cherry crunch
directions: Crumble the first 4 ingredients together; spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to brown it.
Stir often; it browns quickly. Cool.
Press into an 8 x 12-inch glass pan, reserving small amount for topping.
Mix together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; spread over crumb crust.
Top with pie filling and crumbs.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken in butter, then crumb mix.

title: tomato-basil relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and stir well.
Cover and chill.
Yield:
2 cups (serving size: 1/4 cup).

title: mors prune whip
directions: Soak prunes overnight and then stew until tender.
Remove stones and beat the prunes to a smooth pulp.
Make a meringue with egg whites and sugar.
Beat prunes into this mixture and pour into dish that has been well-greased.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat the eggs; add water and salt. Stir in flour slowly until dough is soft and dry. Divide into 3 balls. Roll thin and spread out to dry. When really dry, cut into strips and then into desired widths.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Put in Bundt pan sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chop stick chicken
directions: Put layer of noodles in casserole.
Arrange chicken on noodles.
Follow with celery and onions.
Cover with soup mixture, then rest of noodles.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Longer if refrigerated.

title: honey pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and honey.
Add eggs.
Mix spices together and add to pumpkin.
Add unbeaten light and heavy cream to mixture. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 15 minutes at this temperature to let crust set. then reduce heat to 325° for remainder of time, approximately 50 minutes.
To Serve: top with whipped cream.

title: white potato pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: quick bubble nut bread
directions: Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan; set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into quarters; roll each piece in sugar mixture.
Layer coated piece in pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter; pour over dough.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool bread in pan 10 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
1 (10-inch) ring.

title: black bean rice soup(fast - easy - low calorie)
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in saucepan until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer until rice is tender, about 5 minutes. Makes 7 main dish servings.

title: apricot glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling salt water 10 minutes.
Cool, peel and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Arrange in 2-quart casserole. Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in saucepan. Add nectar and water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened. Stir in butter and nuts.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Slice and layer 9 x 13-inch pan with one roll mix.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over cookie layer.
Slice other roll and layer over cream cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 2 (12-hole) muffin pans; set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream together butter, eggs and sugar. Reserve 3 teaspoons flour.
In medium bowl, combine remaining flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add vanilla to milk. Alternately add milk and flour mixture to creamed butter and egg mixture.
Place berries in large bowl; sprinkle with reserved flour and turn gently with large spoon until berries are lightly coated.
Fold berries into batter.
Fill each muffin pan 3/4 full and sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until muffins pull away from sides of pan and turn golden brown and crumb on sides.

title: white bread
directions: Knead until soft and elastic.
The longer you knead, the better your bread will be.
Cover and let rise in a warm place.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: apple-grape-cabbage salad with honey and sour cream dressing
directions: In large bowl, toss apple with lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Add grapes and cabbage.
Mix to blend sour cream, honey, aniseed, salt and pepper; spoon over salad.
Toss lightly. Chill 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice dish
directions: Cook onion and margarine in frying pan.
Add remaining ingredients and mix in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender, but firm, not mushy.
Drain. Heat sugar
and	vinegar
to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Add salad oil and tomato
soup.
Slice
or chop onion and pepper; add to carrots. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread.
Put in layers the onions, cucumbers, green peppers, celery and chopped tomatoes.
Put in kidney beans.
Mix sweet pickle juice and mayonnaise or salad dressing (Ranch) together.
Pour this on top of cornbread and layer of vegetables. On top of this put shredded cheese.
It is now ready to eat, but the longer it sets, the more tasty it is.
Store in refrigerator in closed container.

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers.
Chop peppers and onions.
Pour boiling water over the vegetables and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain. In a stainless steel or enamel kettle, add other ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add milk egg and onion.
Stir to moisten.
Drop a small tsp. of batter for each puppy into a hot deep fat fryer.
Cook till golden brown.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Beat egg
in
bowl, add cubed bread, then crab meat and seasonings.
Stir; add butter and lemon juice last.
Turn into a greased
dish.
Dot
with
butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water, taken from total amount listed.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, water and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast mixture and flour gradually, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Turn dough out on slightly floured board and knead until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Brush top lightly with melted shortening.
Cover.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Divide into two portions.
Shape into loaves and place in two greased bread pans.
Cover.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mock mincemeat pie
directions: Pare, core and slice the apples.
Chop up the green tomatoes if you are using them.
Combine with the raisins.
Place in a pan with the orange rind, orange juice and cider. Cover and simmer until the apples are very soft.
Stir in the sugar, cinnamon, cloves and crackers until well blended.

title: famous bill's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain well.
Add all ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add condensed milk.
Mix well and add lemon juice.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and top with meringue. Bake until brown.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed garlic bread(club member: kristi mayfield)
directions: Cut ends off of bread and pinch out bread from inside of loaf. Put bread that has been pinched out in bowl and mix with the milk and egg; set aside.
Saute the beef and spices until done, then mix the cheese with beef and spices until melted.
Mix meat mixture and bread mixture together; stuff into French bread shell.
Wrap in tinfoil and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Open foil and pour melted butter mixed with garlic butter and dill weed over top of loaf. Bake 5 to 7 minutes longer.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together; add powdered sugar.
Eat with fresh fruit.
Must be refrigerated.

title: chicken-cheese-chili
directions: Lay chicken breasts in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While chicken cooks, mix cheese and chili.
Cover each breast with mixture; pat to hold in place. Sprinkle evenly with green onion and bacon.
Return to oven, uncovered.
Bake until chicken is white in center of thickest piece and cheese melts, about 10 minutes.
Scatter avocado over top.
Serve with sour cream to taste.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in water and hand squeeze water out.
It's like wet dough.
Work into meat until it's all dissolved.
Add egg, tomato sauce, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Top meat loaf with sauce.

title: cleo's apple slice bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add egg yolk and milk. Roll out half and put in jelly roll pan. Crush 1 cup corn flakes and put on bottom crust. Put apple mixture on crust and roll half of crust; put on top (slit). Froth egg white and spread over top crust. Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice. Drizzle over top when hot. Bake at 400° for 1 hour in 11 x 15-inch pan.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil.
Stir
in peanut butter and cereal.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes approximately 6 dozens.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, whip.
Add milk.
Soften butter and cream cheese in microwave on high 45 seconds.
Whip into potatoes with cheddar cheese and parmesan cheese, green pepper, green onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 2 quart casserole dish. Crumble toast and sprinkle on top.
Microwave on HIGH 10 to 12 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking.
Rest, covered, 5 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Simmer carrots and celery in bouillon water 10 minutes; set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Shred cheese; add to milk mixture, stirring with wooden spoon.
Add vegetables and bouillon mixture.
Keep heating, but do not boil.
Serve topped with chives.

title: tomato salad
directions: Wash tomatoes, slice them thinly or cut in wedges.
Place them in bowl.
In another bowl, mix salt, brown mustard, parsley, basil and onion.
Add vinegar and oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour dressing over tomatoes at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken and rolled dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper. Cook until meat is tender.
Take meat off bones.
Add dumplings.

title: crispy yeast rolls(makes 24 rolls)
directions: Combine warm water with yeast.
Add salt, sugar, shortening, eggs, 1 cup water and flour.
Mix well and knead well on floured board.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Remove to floured board; knead well.
Pull off chunks of dough and roll in ball.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Three cherry-sized balls for each roll.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coffee substitute
directions: One egg in baking (to bind) equals 1 tablespoon soy or garbanzo flour or 3 tablespoons potato flour or instant tapioca.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to a rolling boil in large saucepan.
Add baking mix all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat, about 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time; continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto aluminum foil covered baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with vanilla pudding or sweetened whipped cream and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: texas buffalo chips
directions: Combine butter, sugar, and brown sugar.
After butter is cooled mix in eggs, vanilla, oatmeal, and corn flakes.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and add to mixture. Then add pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by ice cream scoop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-18 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix together apples, cranberry sauce and sugar in bottom of deep casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Combine the brown sugar, flour, chopped pecans and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over top of cranberry mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Fill the pie shell 3/4 full of rhubarb.
Mix sugar, egg yolks, butter and flour.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in other mixture and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; 325° for 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy chicken noodle soup
directions: Mix all ingredients except Noodles-n-Sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Add Noodles-n-Sauce.
Continue to cook for 10 minutes.

title: southern-style catfish
directions: Cut fillets into 4 serving portions.
In flat dish, combine cornmeal with hot 'n spicy seasoned salt and seasoned pepper.
Dip fish in buttermilk, then in flour.
Dip again in buttermilk, then in seasoned cornmeal.

title: beef-barley soup
directions: Place all ingredients in soup pot and simmer for several hours.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix flour, oleo and pecans and press in bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan. Bake until light brown (7 to 10 minutes). Whip cream cheese until smooth; add powdered sugar; beat again.
Add Cool Whip and until smooth.
Spread on crust.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine oil, catsup, vinegar, sugar, onion, salt and pepper. Mix well with beater.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend oats into flour and mix with flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Mix into batter.
Melt Hershey bar and stir into batter.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil in 2-quart pan.
Saute onion and garlic for 1 minute. Add tomato paste, water, sherry, bouillon cube, cheese and seasonings.
Blend and cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer at low speed.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 375°.
Makes 48 cookies.
Press with Kisses as soon as cookies are done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand to soften.
Mince Frankenmuth cheese. Work all ingredients together until cheese is mixed well, then shape into a ball.
Cover with chopped walnuts.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix all in bowl with beater, except coconut.
Stir in coconut. Pour into greased nine-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: garlic-cabbage salad
directions: Place red and white cabbage in separate bowls.
Mix together the garlic and anchovies.
Add vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; stir well (do not mix in food processor).
Divide this mixture evenly between the two bowls of cabbage.

title: molasses pudding("written from memory")
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake in a hot oven until brown. Wonder how it will turn out?

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly combine cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Place 1/4 cup cheese mixture in the center of each chicken breast.
Roll and secure with toothpicks.
In a large skillet, brown chicken on all sides in hot oil; drain fat.
Pour tomato sauce over chicken.
Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini jam(makes 4 pints)
directions: Combine together all ingredients, except jello.
Cook until it boils.
Turn to simmer, 30 minutes.
Remove from burner.
Add 6 ounces of any kind of jello.
Stir until jello dissolves.
Put in jars at once.
Seal and refrigerate.

title: woodsman beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat.
Brown in oil in large Dutch oven.
Drain.
Add any remaining flour mixture, water, wine and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onion.
Bring to boil.
Cover and continue simmering 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Stir in dill and parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mango nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs and then stir in dry ingredients, mango and lime juice.
Mix, then add in chopped nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.
Do not slice until second day.

title: haystacks
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, place chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Cover with lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Add noodles and mix to cover noodles.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool to set.
You can also add raisins or peanuts; also use peanut butter chips in place of chocolate or butterscotch chips.

title: make ahead yeast rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients thoroughly and set aside to cool completely.
Add eggs and yeast.
Work in about 6 cups of all-purpose flour.
Place in a large bowl with lid to contain. Refrigerate overnight.
Make walnut size balls and place 3 to a muffin tin.
Let rise 2 hours.
