Dot with a dab of butter on top of each roll.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until well browned and done.
Makes about 24 rolls.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix in fruit cocktail, cherries and bananas.
Add nuts and fold in whipped cream.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze.
Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: guatemala marinade
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, horseradish, lemon juice, Accent, dry mustard and salt and pour over the following and marinate overnight:
black olives, water chestnuts, cauliflower, shrimp, zucchini and tomatoes.
Makes a nice salad lunch.

title: mom's hobo dinner
directions: Take hamburger meat and make into 4 patties.
Place each on a sheet of foil.
Cut potatoes, onions and carrots and place on each patty.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and seasoned salt over top.
Fold foil into an airtight package.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In mixing bowl pour boiling water over shortening and margarine.
When liquid has cooled to lukewarm add yeast and stir until dissolved. Add egg and salt to liquid. Sift flour into mixture about 3/4 cup at a time.
Add enough to make soft dough. Shape rolls out, then let rise. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 20 rolls.

title: sherbet shower surprise
directions: Scoop all of sherbet into a large punch bowl.
Add pineapple juice and soda on top of sherbet.
Stir constantly, while adding soda.
Makes approximately 15 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge or chocolate fudge
directions: Mix milk and butter (melt butter); add sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Use peanut butter for peanut butter fudge.)

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In skillet, saute first 4 ingredients.
In 3-quart pot, combine soup, pimento, parsley, onion mixture, cooked meat and one-half of cheese.
Bring to boil, then lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes. In 3-quart dish, place spaghetti and stir in butter.
Add meat-soup mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Stir apples into sugar, flour and cinnamon mixture.
Pour into pie shell; sprinkle with water.
Cover with crumb topping made by mixing 1/2 cup of butter or margarine, 1/2 cup of brown sugar and flour.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix the biscuit mix, sausage and cheese with a wooden spoon - or you might want to mix with your hands.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
These will freeze nicely.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Make hamburger balls about size of walnuts. Fry about half done. Drain on paper towels. Put in oven dish or slow cooker. Add chili sauce and 2 bottles of water, measured in chili sauce bottles. Add grape jelly. Cook in oven at 375° for 1 hour or in slow cooker overnight.

title: basil cream sauce
directions: In a large frying pan, saute garlic in oil until tender but not brown.
Add basil.
Continue sauteing for a few seconds. Remove garlic cloves.
Add tomatoes and cook for 20 to 30 minutes. Shut off and add 1/2 cup heavy cream or more to your taste.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine 1/3 cup of the cheese soup and the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape into loaf in shallow baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Place on platter.
Heat remaining soup; pour over loaf to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chinese mabo tofu
directions: Heat oil in a skillet or wok at medium heat.
Brown meat and add mixed vegetables.
Add Mabo tofu sauce and simmer.
After drained, gently stir in cubed tofu and simmer again.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Mix well and press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool well.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into beaten egg white. Roll into chopped nuts.
Bake 1 inch apart on cookie sheet in 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and put thumbprint in. Return to oven and bake for 8 minutes.
Fill print with icing or jelly.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Bake in oblong pan.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: Place chicken, mushrooms and water chestnuts in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and soup.
Pour soup mix over chicken and vegetable mix.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain juice from beets and set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix good and add beet juice.
Stir well and add melted butter and vinegar.
Add the beets; heat thoroughly until beets are heated through and through.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt; mix by hand.
Stir in chocolate bits; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla, beating well.
Mixture will appear unmixable at first.
Keep beating.
Use muffin tins and paper liners, filling 1/2 to 3/4 full with dark mixture (flour and cocoa).
Drop one tablespoon of cheese mixture on top of each one.
Bake about 20 minutes.
These freeze well.
Serves 24.

title: buenillo's(mexican wedding cookies)
directions: Mix eggs, milk, vanilla, flour, 1 teaspoon sugar and salt together to make a batter.

title: easy breakfast
directions: Line muffin pans with strips of bacon.
Crack one egg into each muffin cup.
Bake at 375° until done.
Serve with toast, sliced tomato or juice.

title: ever-ready bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Mix.
Cover and store in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Bake as many as you need whenever needed in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and pepper. Cook over medium heat until tender, but not brown. Remove from heat; add flour and stir until smooth. Gradually add broth and milk, stirring as added. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Mix sauce, bread crumbs and turkey. Season to taste with salt. Press mixture into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until loaf has browned evenly. When done, turn onto hot platter. Serve hot or cold with or without sauce.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Beat egg, add to water and yeast. Add 1/4
cup
sugar
and 1 1/4 sticks oleo.
Mix 4 cups flour into other
ingredients.
Put
in
tight container and put in refrigerator.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Prepare 13-inch baking dish by spraying with vegetable spray.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla and beat.
Add dry ingredients, zucchini and nuts.
Add pineapple or applesauce, if desired.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to package directions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chop rhubarb (or apples) and place on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb.
Pour 2 cups half and half on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: flaky pastry
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together.
Blend with fork into dry ingredients.
Chill crust 15 minutes before rolling. Makes enough for 2 double crust pies.

title: worth waiting for casserole
directions: Layer potatoes and onions in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle garlic powder, salt and pepper over vegetables.
Spoon browned and drained ground beef over top.

title: "judy o'grady's ham"
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Mix everything, including noodles, together.
Bake, covered, in a buttered casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.
Then remove the cover and sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Dot with butter and brown under broiler.

title: savory sausage rice
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet; pour off excess fat.
Add green pepper, onion and celery; saute.
Combine soup mix and boiling water in large saucepan; stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add sausage mixture, salt and almonds; stir well.
Pour into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage and vegetable casserole
directions: Cook sausages as directed on package. Drain and cool slightly; cut in half. Cook vegetables according to package; drain. Spoon half the vegetables into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with half the cheese, arranging the remaining cheese triangles around the outside edge of the casserole. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts and mixture is heated through. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: simple party punch
directions: Note:
Do not substitute for any other brand of sherbet.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ham loaves
directions: In a bowl, combine pork, ham, crumbs, eggs and milk.
Shape into 12 oval loaves, using 1 cup of mixture for each.
Place in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: viennese nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and add all other ingredients.
Roll into the size of a walnut.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot and then when they get cold, roll in sugar again.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour in pie shells and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, water and syrup in pan and boil until it crackles in cold water.
Add peanuts and cook slowly until the peanuts are roasted.
Add vanilla, margarine and baking soda.
While it is still foaming, pour on greased cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.

title: french apple streusel
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, mix flour and salt. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup.
Add milk to egg to make 2/3 cup.
Stir milk mixture into flour.
Stir until mixture holds together.

title: rangetop custard
directions: In a large measuring cup or medium bowl, stir eggs, eggnog and vanilla until well blended.
Pour equal amount in each of 4 greased 6 ounce custard cups. Place on rack in a large skillet. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Add boiling water to skillet to cover bottom half of cups.
Cover skillet with lid or foil.
Cook over low heat with water on gentle simmer for 12 to 15 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean.

title: walnut cream candy
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until it threads.
Add syrup to 2 beaten egg whites slowly.
Add to above mixture the butter, vanilla and baking powder.
Beat all until thickened, then add the cup of nuts.
Stir.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: fabulous funnel cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined milk and egg, mixing until smooth.
Pour batter into 1 inch of hot oil.
Form a 4-inch spiral.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: valentine quiche without a crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 10-inch ceramic quiche dish or 11-inch pie pan, using 1/2 butter.
Spread bread crumbs on baking sheet.
Place in oven.
Toast, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Spread in dish.
Melt remaining butter in skillet.
Saute onion.
Stir occasionally until golden, 3 to 5 minutes.
Using heart shaped cookie cutter, cut six hearts from ham.
Coarsely chop scraps of ham.
Sprinkle over bread.
Layer onion and cheese.
Beat eggs, flour, half and half, salt and pepper well, not frothy.
Pour egg mixture over.
Arrange ham hearts on top.
Bake 50 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese. Add pineapple, coconut and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: quick trifle(can be made 24 hours before serving)
directions: Tear cake into chunks and place in large glass bowl.
Combine dry gelatin with semi-thawed berries.
Mix well.
Pour over cake. Pour prepared pudding over berries.
Add sliced bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: bun candy
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together.
Spread 1/2 mixture over pan.
Chill.
Cook margarine, milk and pudding.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add powdered sugar and spread over base.
Add peanuts to remaining chip mixture and spread over top.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: polynesian style chicken
directions: In large skillet or a wok, heat oil over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry, until meat is firm and white (about 5 minutes).
Add pineapple and green pepper; stir-fry for 1 minute. Stir in pineapple juice and Yoshida's sauces.
Simmer for 2 minutes and garnish with sesame seed.
Serves 4.
Serve with rice.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill 2 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables as a dip.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour in buttered pan.
Mix and pour remaining ingredients over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chocolate gravy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and salt.
Stir over medium heat until smooth and thick.
Serve hot with homemade biscuits.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of loaf pan.
In large bowl, blend first four ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder and blend until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.

title: monkey pad bread
directions: Put all cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar in a plastic bag.
Cut up biscuits in 4 pieces each and shake in bag until covered.
Place in tube pan or in saucepan.
Mix cinnamon, sugar and melted margarine.
Put mixture over biscuits and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Serve warm, if you desire.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and water; cook to soft-ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat; add chocolate squares and stir until chocolate melts.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add evaporated milk; mix thoroughly.
Cool.
This should be heated over hot water for hot fudge sundaes.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat, onion, celery and bell pepper in skillet.
Drain and add to broth and rice.
Cook in medium-sized saucepan until rice is done.
You may like the flavor you get if you put meat mixture in blender for a second or two, then pour in rice.

title: 14 carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Add oil, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Then blend thoroughly.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool; frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: (Meatballs will have finer texture if meats are ground together twice.)
Soak bread crumbs in milk or cream 5 minutes.
Add ground meats, eggs, onion, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/4 teaspoon dill weed, allspice, nutmeg and cardamom.
Mix well and refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and brown lightly in hot butter.

title: crisp fried onion rings
directions: Peel onions and cut into 1/2-inch slices and separate into rings.
Place rings in large bowl; cover with water and refrigerate 1 hour.
Drain well and dry with paper towels.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add seasoning mix and 1/2 cup water. Simmer until water cooks down (about 5 minutes).
Warm tortillas until soft.
Combine can of soup, sour cream and half of the cheese.
Mix and set aside.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, one egg, and vegetable oil together until the mixture is crumbly.
Reserve one cup of mixture for topping. Pour the remainder of the mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
While crust is baking, beat together cream cheese, sugar and one egg until light and smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips and spread the mixture over the baked crust.
Sprinkle the reserved crumb mixture over the cream cheese mixture and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 3 dozen small bars.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add crackers and baking powder alternately with milk to cream mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour into three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend all ingredients, except crust, together in electric mixer or blender.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.
Brown meringue under broiler until lightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: apricot whole wheat bread
directions: In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Combine milk, honey, egg and oil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to dampen flour.
Gently stir in apricots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Remove; let stand 10 minutes.
Cut.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Saute onion and celery in margarine in a nonstick skillet until clear.
Mix broccoli, soup and cheese; add to celery and onion.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Put into nonstick 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Top with crackers that have been mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: ring bologna and onions
directions: Slice bologna in 1/2-inch slices.
Slice onions.
Brown bologna; remove.
Add oil and margarine.
Cook onions some, then add bologna and salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring to boil white sugar, brown sugar and Karo syrup and add peanut butter, salted peanuts and corn flakes.
Lightly crush corn flakes.
Press firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: grandpa's spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend soup mix and sour cream.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: glorified deviled eggs
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour. Add tomatoes, onions and seasonings.
Cook and stir until thick. Spoon a little bit of the tomato mixture in bottom of a baking dish.
Put eggs on top of this. Cover with remaining tomato mixture.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over the top and bake at 425° until crumbs begin to brown.

title: company calico beans
directions: Brown beef and bacon; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients except tomatoes.
Mix well and pour tomatoes over top. Bake covered in a large crock-pot or roaster for 3 hours at 325°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Drain artichoke hearts well and either mash or chop finely.
Mix into mayonnaise mixture and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 250° until bubbly and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Melt oleo.
Brown, watch and stir; burns easily.
Add the oil, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cool.
Mix 20 minutes before eating.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use large casserole.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Place ingredients in a bowl and put in the microwave until margarine melts.
Remove from microwave and whip until creamy smooth.

title: creamy braised chicken
directions: In Dutch oven or large kettle, saute sliced onion, carrot and celery in 1 tablespoon butter until tender.
Remove veggies and set aside.
Add chicken to pan; brown on both sides.
Remove and keep warm.
Add wine; simmer until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Stir in broth and seasoning.
Return chicken to pan; cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until juice runs clear.
Remove chicken to a serving platter; keep warm.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan, stirring until mixture is the consistency of mashed potatoes and forms a ball.
Knead until cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: pumpernickel bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup tepid water in a large mixing bowl; let
stand about 10 minutes.
Scald milk.
Add shortening, butter,
molasses,	salt, cocoa and caraway seed.
Stir. Add
1 cup
room
temperature water and check for temperature between 110° to 140°.
Pour this mixture into bowl with yeast and
stir in	cornmeal.
Add	3
cups
bread flour and mashed potatoes; beat thoroughly.
Add 3 cups rye flour a little at a time
and
blend. Add
rye
flour
until dough consistency is reached
and
knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; cover
with
a
damp towel.
Rise until double in bulk.	Punch down;
knead
lightly
1 to 2 minutes.
Divide in two;
shape into	rolls
and
place on a cookie sheet sprinkled with cornmeal;
rise
until	double	in bulk.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake
for
to 35 minutes. Place on a cooling rack;
baste with melted butter and cover with a damp towel for soft crust.

title: chicken pleaser
directions: Add whatever ingredients you want; for example, green peppers, celery, mushrooms or whatever you enjoy.

title: sweet sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil well.
Pour over remaining ingredients; toss.
Cover and chill 3 to 24 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Great side dish with brats or Polish sausage.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; drain off grease.
Add 1/2 can of each kind of soup to meat mixture.
Cook egg noodles in salt water; drain and rinse noodles in hot water.
Add the other 1/2 can of each soup to noodles.
Place noodle mixture in casserole dish, then place meat mixture on top.
Add cheese on top.
Put in oven at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix warm water, sugar, yeast and salt; let this mixture set about 5 minutes until yeast has dissolved.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Add stick of melted margarine, then add flour; you can use mixer to beat in 4 cups, but the last 2 have to be done by hand with a spoon.
Original recipe calls for all-purpose flour.
I use Gold Medal Better for Bread flour.
It is different from regular flour and makes rolls taste better.
Knead in same bowl that you have mixed all this in.
Add enough flour to get dough to where it is not sticky.
Place dough in well-greased bowl.
Turn it over so top will be greased also.
Lay a damp cloth on top and put bowl in a warm place.
This will rise in about 1 1/2 hours.
Make out rolls into 4 pie plates and let rise again.
Bake at eat.
I bake at 400° until brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry ground beef, onions and celery in large skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add the soups and corn and simmer.
Cook the macaroni; drain and then mix with meat mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until celery is tender.

title: baked parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Combine first five ingredients; set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in baking dish, coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: In blender, put flour, salt, baking powder, milk and egg. Blend.
Add corn.
Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.

title: rice dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: tex-mex chili
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally to break up meat.
Pour off fat. Stir in soup, kidney beans with their liquid, chili powder and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into bowls; top with sour cream and sliced green onions.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups (6 servings).

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, prepare noodles.
Drain and return to saucepan.
Over low heat, heat noodles, cream, oleo, salt, pepper and cheese.
Toss well before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate mint brownies
directions: Prepare batter following directions on box for "cake-like" brownies (this recipe is doubled).
Mix all ingredients and 3/4 cup mint chocolate chips in a medium bowl.
Spread batter in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ground beef, oil, peppers, onion, salt and pepper; cook until brown and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour 1/2 of mixture into greased pan.
Layer meat mixture and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Add remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: toll house cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with dash of salt and vanilla until soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients, then add the next 2 ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine first four ingredients and bring to boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: herb marinade
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting lid, or in a cruet; shake well.
This will keep well for at least 2 weeks, if refrigerated.

title: cherry delight
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish. Mix pudding according to directions.
Pour pudding over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Spread pie filling over Cool Whip as evenly as possible.

title: tamale pie (mexican)
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef. Drain. Add tomatoes, onions and spices. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Arrange 5 tortillas in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, tearing tortillas as needed. Cover with half of meat mixture, then half of cheese. Repeat layers, using remaining tortillas, meat mixture and cheese. Sprinkle with olives. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Let stand a few minutes before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine lettuce, onions, celery, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, sugar, cheese, salt, garlic and frozen peas.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: famous anchor bar buffalo chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at 2 joints; discard tips.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
Add half wings and cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and crisp.
Remove; drain well.
Repeat with remaining wings.
Melt butter in saucepan and add hot sauce and vinegar, amount of hot sauce depends on the degree of hotness desired.
Pour butter mixture over wings, coating evenly.
Serve with Bleu cheese dressing and celery sticks.

title: rob's brisket
directions: Rub brisket with olive oil and season with black pepper, red pepper and garlic powder.
Place 1 cup oil in large, heavy pan with lid.
Heat on medium heat until hot.
Brown brisket on both sides for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layer of meat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of sliced onions on top of meat.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix the can of soup with the water.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° to 400° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine top three ingredients in large bowl and toss together.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir into salad mixture.
Top with layer of Parmesan cheese, then Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple refrigerator chiffon cake
directions: Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Separate eggs.
Combine slightly beaten egg yolks, 1 cup crushed pineapple and its syrup, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly, until custard consistency.
Stir in softened gelatine until thoroughly dissolved; cool.
Slowly beat 1/3 cup sugar into beaten egg whites; fold in.
Whip 2/3 cup icy cold evaporated milk until triple in volume; add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and beat until very thick; fold in.
Spoon 1/4 of mixture into waxed paper-lined 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Add a layer of large thin chocolate cookies; repeat 3 times.
Add remaining chiffon as last layer.
Chill overnight; unmold for 8 to 10 servings.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Brown hamburger meat.
Combine rice, hamburger meat, mushroom soup, chicken soup and milk.
Mix well with spoon. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: Bring water to a boil and add walnuts.
Heat to boiling and cook for 1 minute.
Rinse walnuts under running hot water and drain.
Pour walnuts into large bowl and gently stir in sugar until dissolved.
(If necessary, let stand for 5 minutes to dissolve sugar.)

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut, beef and cheese in casserole.
Pour dressing on top.
Crumble bread and toss with oleo. Spread on top and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: *Note: Marie makes the gravy, which I'm certain is much better than the jar variety!

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until brown; add consomme and Worcestershire.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Season with salt.
Pour soup into individual bowls.
Float toasted bread on top.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in a big pot.
Drain excess fat. Add water, bouillon, pepper, chili seasoning and taco mix.
Stir over medium heat until it simmers.
Add kidney beans, corn, tomato sauce, tomatoes and macaroni.
Bring back to simmer and let simmer 15 minutes to blend flavors.

title: texan style casserole
directions: In a small bowl, blend 1 cup beef broth, tomato paste and taco seasoning mix; set aside.
In saucepan over high heat, combine remaining beef broth and enough water to equal 1 3/4 cup liquid; heat to boil.
Add rice and cook according to package directions.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; pour off fat.

In 2 quart casserole dish, layer 1/3 each of the rice, corn, and meat mixture and reserved sauce; repeat layers twice, combining the last portion of meat and sauce for the top layer. Cover; bake a 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until hop.
Garnish with corn chips and diced tomatoes.
Make 4 to 6 servings.

title: german kuchen
directions: Blend together eggs, sugar and Crisco.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread batter in pan, saving 1 cup of batter for top.
Cover with pie filling.
Take saved batter and drop by teaspoons over top of filling; go through with knife. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or less.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Day Ahead:
With fork, score cucumbers lengthwise, then cut crosswise into thin slices.
Slice onions thinly.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage, onion and green pepper.
Add and simmer, mushrooms, pizza sauce and spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles as directed.
Layer in crock-pot (twice): noodles, beef mixture, pepperoni and cheeses.
Cook on low until cheese melts, about 30 minutes.
May also be layered in baking pan and baked at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Work all ingredients together and make in little balls.
Cook 15 minutes at 325°.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Put in dry ingredients.
Bake on ungreased pan at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: easy cheese quesadillas (appetizer)
directions: Put one tortilla on microwave-safe plate.
Sprinkle a small amount of cheese around each tortilla, being sure to spread out to edge.
Spoon some salsa over cheese, a very small amount.
Top with another tortilla.
Put in microwave for 30 to 40 seconds.
Take out and let set for a couple of minutes, then cut into 4 triangles (across each way).
Repeat with other tortillas.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Cook rice until dry and fluffy.
Put 1/2 in small buttered casserole, cover with 1/2 pineapple and sugar.
Dot with butter. Add second layer in same manner and bake in moderate oven until slightly brown on top.
Serve as vegetable with ham.

title: provencale fresh tomato relish
directions: Use tomatoes held at room temperature until fully ripe.
Dice tomatoes and set aside.
In small bowl, combine vinegar, mustard, water and salt.
Add onion, capers and tomatoes; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with or on chicken, fish or meat.

title: english trifle
directions: To Assemble:
Split ladyfingers, making 4 layers in all.
Layer in deep glass bowl 12 ladyfingers.
Spread with preserves jam side up.
Sprinkle with almonds and cover with about 3/4 cup of custard; sprinkle with sherry.
Continue procedure, making 3 layers each the same.
Top with 4th layer of ladyfingers and sprinkle with sherry. Chill about four hours.
Decorate top with whipped cream (beaten with confectioners sugar), raspberries and the remaining almonds.

title: baked perch fillets
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with onion slices.
Add layer of mushrooms.
Place fish fillets on top.
Cover with bread crumbs. Sprinkle with parsley.
Pour broth over all.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes per inch of thickness at thickest part.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil the chicken and debone.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Saute bell pepper and onion in butter.
Pour in soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Strain spaghetti.
Add soup mix and chicken and Velveeta cheese.
Mix all together until cheese melts. Very good!!

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites, gradually add sugar.
Mix together crushed Ritz crackers, baking powder and nuts.
Mix with egg and sugar mixture.
Pour in lightly buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except ketchup.
Shape into a loaf pan. Top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: egg 'n muffin
directions: Place bacon between 2 paper towels.
Cook in Radarange oven on Full power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Set aside.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop fine.
Cook 15 minutes.
Let stand and drain off half juice.
Chop other vegetables and add to tomatoes. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Tie cinnamon sticks, mustard and cloves in a cloth bag.
Add to vegetables with brown sugar, salt and vinegar.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours, until vegetables are soft.
Pack in pint jars according to canning instructions.

title: borani
directions: Wash the spinach and drain.
Remove the stems and any discolored leaves.
In a heavy 2 or 3-quart saucepan, bring 1/2 cup water to a boil over high heat.
Add the spinach; reduce the heat to low and simmer tightly covered for about 10 minutes.
Drain the spinach; allow it to cool and squeeze out as much water as possible.
Chop the spinach very finely.
In a deep bowl, combine the spinach, lemon juice, onion, salt and a few grindings of pepper.
Toss the mixture with a spoon, then stir in the yoghurt and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate at least an hour.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves before serving.

title: fig cookies
directions: Mix and drop on greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot crab meat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with milk until creamy.
Add onion, horseradish and crab meat and mix until blended.
Place in small baking dish and sprinkle with paprika and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peachy yogurt breakfast sundae
directions: Place peaches in small bowl; top with yogurt and wheat germ. Garnish with blueberries.
Serves 1, about 190 calories and 3 g fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add broccoli.
Add mushroom soup, cheese and cooked rice. Pour into casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: rose petal jelly
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in a blender until very fine.
Add sugar, blend about 5 minutes.
Add pectin and water.
Bring to a boil for about 1 minute.
Put into jars and cover with wax.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Mix diced potatoes, sour cream, salt, cottage cheese and green onions in large bowl.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
If mixture seems too dry you can add a little more sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: heaven and earth potatoes
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese and paprika. Spread in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until cheese is melted and potatoes are heated through.
Could be made a day ahead and heated the next day.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan combine sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Spread in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares when firm.
Makes 3 pounds of candy.

title: linguine salad
directions: Break the linguine in thirds before cooking.
Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight.
You can add seafood to this to make it a main course.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and bake in 350° oven until done and skins begin to crisp, approximately 40 minutes.

Remove from oven and cut in half lengthwise; scoop potato out of skins very carefully. Mix potato, butter, milk, sour cream, bacon, garlic, 1/2 of green onion, red onion and 1 cup of cheese, salt and pepper.
Make sure potato is mashed smooth.
After mixing, spoon back into skins, dividing evenly between the 12 skins.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese; sprinkle with the remaining green onion.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted and beginning to bubble. Cool for 10 minutes and serve with a small dollop of sour cream on top.
Serves family or group of 8.

title: spanish rice
directions: Chop and saute in oleo the onions and peppers until onions turn yellow.
Add hamburger; saute until brown, then add tomatoes, raw rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in covered casserole about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
In last 15 minutes, remove cover and brown.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain well.
Mix together broccoli, onion, eggs, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and salt.
Add Cheddar cheese. Stir in one package of Jiffy corn bread mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Reduce to 325° if using glass bowl or pan.

title: judson college banana bread(from judson college dietician in 1940's)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add well-beaten eggs.
Add mashed bananas.
Sift together flour and soda and add gradually to mixture. Stir in vanilla and nuts and bake in slow oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until firm in center.
Use long pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain and cut into small pieces, set aside.
Mix the following together:
egg, onion, butter, soup, bread cubes and cheese.
Add broccoli.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Makes approximately 15 biscuits.

title: cheesy cauliflower casserole
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in 2-quart casserole in order listed. Blend flour, salt, pepper and butter in saucepan.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add half and half and processed cheese, stirring until smooth.
Pour over vegetables and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Top with cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese and bake for 3 minutes longer.
Yields 12 servings.

title: wedding soup
directions: Boil chicken for 2 to 3 hours.
Add onion and celery last hour.
Shred with fork.

title: low-fat pie
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into large graham cracker crust or 2 small ones.
Will also fill 18 mini graham cracker crusts.
Top with fresh fruit to make a delicious cheese cake.

title: german potato casserole
directions: Boil potato slices until tender; mix sour cream, onion soup mix, mushroom soup, lemon juice and mustard.
Heat sauerkraut in 2 tablespoons pork drippings.
Alternate layers of potatoes, cream mixture and sauerkraut.
Place bread crumbs on top and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salmon supper cakes
directions: Drain salmon reserving liquid.
Remove skin and bones.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir up Cool Whip.
To soften, pour in crushed pineapple juice and all.
Stir until all lumps are gone.
Stir in marshmallows until coated.
With Cool Whip
and pineapple mixture, then add pudding until the mixture is a light mint green.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine 1/4 cup evaporated milk, cake mix and margarine; mix well.
Press half of mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drizzle with caramel.
Top with spoonfuls of remaining cake mix.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean, wash and dry the spinach.
Chill well.
Trim bacon of excess fat.
Saute the bacon over medium heat until soft, not crisp.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, vinegar and sugar. Stir and heat.
Pour over spinach and toss well.
Serve with fresh ground pepper.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, sugar and pecans.
Cut in oleo.
Pat into bottom of 2-quart flat Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Save some for top by baking in a small pie pan (crumble and sprinkle on top).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cocoa mix(in a jar)
directions: To make mix: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 2 - quart jar or tall container.
Seal with a lid and decorate with fabric and ribbon.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Add seafood and other ingredients; mix well.
Pour in a greased 4-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and cream of mushroom soup together.
Add green beans.
Stir all together and put in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take out and add the fried onions to top.
Put back in oven to brown the onions.

title: rock cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mrs. burrier's white fruitcake
directions: Assemble all fruit, cut as suggested.
Sift flour and measure. Add soda, baking powder and salt and sift all together 3 times. Sift one cup of mixture over fruit.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add remaining flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice, fruits and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased, paper lined pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours. Increase to 300°.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: potato filling casserole
directions: Cube bread and onion and brown in margarine.
Mix eggs with potatoes and seasonings.
Combine with bread and onion.
Spoon into greased casserole and pour milk over all.
Bake 3/4 to 1 hour in 350° oven.
You may also use 1/2 pound ground beef, turkey or chicken.
May be browned with onions and bread cubes.

title: special potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, eggs, onion, bacon and mayonnaise. Mix well and chill.

title: crunchy green pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water (steamed, if fresh).
Drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream.
Mix prepared dressing, mustard and garlic together.
Pour over salad; toss gently.
Chill.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first three ingredients and spread in bottom of pan. bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix next three ingredients for second layer.
Mix next three ingredients for third layer.

title: texas brownies
directions: Combine flour and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Combine butter, shortening, water and cocoa; stir and heat to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla. Mix well on high with mixer.
Pour into well buttered jelly roll pan (17 1/2 x 11-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Prepare frosting while brownies bake.

title: jackpot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together; add tomato soup, water and noodles.
Cook until tender.
Add corn, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in a well-greased 2-quart casserole and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crab cheese dip
directions: Drain can of crab.
Mix all ingredients together, except the grated cheese.
Place in ovenproof casserole and then sprinkle grated cheese on top of mixture.
Bake in oven at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: country-style smothered chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Transfer to paper towels to drain, reserving drippings in pan. Crumble bacon; set aside.
Over medium heat in hot drippings, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat. Add soup, garlic and basil; stir until smooth.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add onion.
Cover; cook 15 minutes more or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with reserved bacon.
Garnish with basil, if desired.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: calizone dough
directions: Fit metal blade into food processor; add all dry ingredients and olive oil.
Slowly add water while processing on "knead," until dough forms a ball.
Place dough in an oiled bowl and let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Fill with Calizone Filling and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Cut tomatoes in half.
Place, cut side up, on baking sheet and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake for 7 hours.
(Check periodically to prevent burning.)
Divide basil, garlic and capers between 2 (8 ounce) jars with tight fitting lids.
When tomatoes are dry and shriveled up, remove from oven. Dip in vinegar; divide tomatoes in jars and cover with olive oil. Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together peanut butter, xxx sugar and cream cheese.
Then add Cool Whip. Beat until creamy.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Can also be made in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cut into squares. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: mint brownies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Frost cooled brownies.

title: country spareribs with sauerkraut
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Place into a roaster or crock-pot.
Add potatoes, apple, caraway seed and kraut.
Cover with water and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Keep checking to see if water is needed.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: In a large bowl place chocolate bits, Marshmallow Creme, German sweet chocolate and walnuts.
In a saucepan place sugar, salt, oleo and evaporated milk.
Heat to boiling and boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over dry ingredients.
Mix quickly until all ingredients are blended and melted.
Pour into jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Score into small pieces.
When well cooled, cut into pieces.
Makes 5 pounds.
Freezes well and makes great gifts.

title: sand tarts
directions: Do First: Mix baking soda and 1 tablespoon water in small container and set aside while creaming butter. Mix butter and sugar with your hand. (Keep one hand dry for answering the phone.) The heat from your hand will help it mix better. Add eggs. Beat until light. Alternately add flour and baking soda/water mix to the creamed ingredients. Continue adding flour until dough is stiff. Test the dough by touching

with dry fingertips. Continue alternately adding the flour and baking soda/water mix until the dough no longer sticks to your fingers. Cover the bowl and chill dough overnight. On lightly floured surface, roll dough very, very thin and cut with star. or other cookie shapes. Put on greased cookie sheets. Brush lightly on top of cookies with mixture of egg yolk and water (mixed well). Decorate with granulated sugar and cinnamon and nuts or other colored sugars as desired. Bake Sand Tarts at 350° until dough is set (not brown), about 8 minutes.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Grease casserole well.
Put 3 or 4 layers of potatoes in the bottom.
Salt and pepper.
Top with half of the salmon.
Add peas on top of salmon, three more layers of potatoes, salt and pepper and rest of salmon.
Finish with the carrots mixed with onion.
Pat down gently.
Pour diluted soup over casserole.
Top with crumbs. Dot with margarine (optional).
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix with blackberries.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Add blackberry mixture.
Dot with butter. Adjust top crust and seal pastry edges.
Cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: super meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and Cool Whip together and add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese.
Take off stove.
Add sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Add egg and mix with fork. Press half of the crumb mix into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spoon cherry pie filling over first layer. Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream or dust with powdered sugar.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve together the jello and hot water.
Add picante sauce or Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.
Pour in mold and serve with chicken salad.

title: caramel butternut cake
directions: Using layered directions, bake and cool cake as directed on package, adding 1 cup chopped pecans to batter.
In a saucepan, heat brown sugar, butter and milk; boil and stir for 2 minutes. Cool 30 minutes.
Gradually add powdered sugar; mix until smooth. Add more powdered sugar to thicken or milk to thin, if needed. Spread between layers, on sides and on top of cake.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped pecans over top of cake.

title: crisco's yellow cake
directions: Measure into a mixing bowl the cake flour, sugar, milk, Crisco and salt. Beat vigorously by hand or mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes. Stir in the baking powder. Add the milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly by hand mixer (medium speed) for 2 minutes.
Pour into two deep 9-inch layer pans (1 1/2-inches deep), which have been rubbed with Crisco or lined with heavy waxed paper.
For smaller pans, fill half full. Bake cupcakes with remaining batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool cakes on a rack 15 minutes before removing from pan. Ice between layers, on sides and top of cake.
Makes two 9-inch layers.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar together.
Add 1/2 cup of milk and egg yolks and stir well.
Add lemon rind and juice and rest of milk.
Pour immediately into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until custard is set and crust is browned at 425° for 10 minutes and 375° for 50 minutes.
Remove and add meringue as follows: 2 egg whites plus 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Beat egg whites at highest mixer speed.
Add sugar at lowest mixer speed.
Bake combination about 8 1/2 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Add soup, sour cream and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Put in a 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover completely with grated cheese.

title: dewberry pie
directions: Fill pie shell with berries. Combine sugar, eggs, flour, sour cream, and salt. Pour mixture over berries and let settle to the bottom of fruit.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place clean chicken breasts in a shallow baking dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
Pat top with butter.
Cover with tinfoil and cook in oven for 1 hour at 350°. Reduce heat to 275° and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix salt and flour; add milk gradually to form a smooth paste. Add eggs, beaten very lightly.
Cover bottom of hot pan, 11 x 13-inch, with fat.
Pour in mixture 1/2-inch thick.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve with brown gravy.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add nuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Cool.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
(Add muffin mix last.)
Bake in glass 11 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot wine cranberry punch
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooker.
Heat 1 to 2 hours on low. Strain and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add apples, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, soda and cloves.
Mix all together.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 or 35 minutes.
Good with a sauce or Cool Whip.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add egg, raisins, applesauce, spices and flour.
Mix soda in 2 tablespoons hot water; pour into flour mixture; add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mama's smothered pork chops
directions: Season pork chops, sprinkle with self-rising flour, fry until brown on both sides.
Slice onion and saute, spread over pork chops.
Mix flour and Botique in one cup water, pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce.
Place in a large bowl.
Layer onion, celery, green pepper, carrots and peas.
Cover with cheese.
Top with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Keep refrigerated overnight. Sprinkle with bacon before serving.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Cook in microwave (covered) for 7 minutes.
Warm up as needed.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef and bacon in electric skillet.
Stir until beef is browned.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Blend flour and seasonings into meat and stir in soup.
Cook, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Serve in buns.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon in a 3-quart saucepan until crisp.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons fat in the pan.
Cook and stir onion and celery in bacon fat until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in salt, pepper, corn and potatoes and heat through.
Stir in bacon.
Sprinkle each serving with parsley and paprika.
Serves 6.

title: party zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onions in boiling water about 5 minutes. Drain well in colander.
While the vegetables drain, melt the stick of butter and combine it with the stuffing.
Mix together the vegetables with the grated carrots, sour cream and chicken soup. Taste for seasoning.
Now put half the buttered stuffing in the bottom of a casserole.
Add the zucchini mixture, then top with the rest of the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix together; pour over favorite beef.
Marinate several hours and grill or cook, as desired.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: supper corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Pour off drippings, leaving 2 to 3 tablespoons in pan.
Cook onion until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and dash of pepper.
Heat to boiling and simmer a minute or two.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: You will also need 2 feet of wax paper.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: apple cranberry relish
directions: This refreshing relish requires no cooking.
Simply put through the food chopper the first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar and walnuts.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Makes about 2 cups.
Serve with turkey, chicken or duckling.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grate or cut up cabbage, peppers and onion. Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Pour into a large pan; cover with foil paper and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli
according
to directions for five minutes and drain.
Combine
beaten
eggs, soup, cheese and mayonnaise. Fold into broccoli and pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs and	dot
with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scandinavian pastry
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put cottage cheese through sieve.
Cream butter & cottage cheese.
Stir salt into flour and mix into butter.
Form into walnut-size balls.
Roll each ball out on floured board.
Put 1 tsp. jelly or jam in middle of each pastry. Brush edges of pastry with water, fold in half and seal edges. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: delicious blond brownies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Mix brown sugar and butter and beat well.
Add egg and vanilla and blend.
Add flour mixture (mixture set aside), a little at a time, mixing well before adding more.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips across top and place in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan.
Prepare noodles according to directions; drain.
In large skillet brown ground meat with celery; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into baked pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: walnut chicken peruvian style
directions: Cook the chicken in boiling water until tender, about 25 minutes.
Shred chicken and set aside.
In a separate container, soak the crust-less bread in the milk.
Add the chili powder and mix.
Place the onion in a skillet with oil and saute.
When the oil comes to a boil add the salt, cumin, coriander, and pepper to taste.
Cook the mixture for a while.
Then add the soaked bread, mashed smooth.
Next add the shredded chicken and the grated cheese.
Simmer for 20 minutes covered, checking to see that the mixture does not burn.
Then, add the walnuts, stirring to blend them in.
Serve hot, garnished with hard-boiled eggs.
Yield:

title: chocolate almond bark bars
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter.
Add cereal, and spread into a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan, or if you make a larger batch, spread in buttered jelly roll pan.

title: awesome cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat softened cream cheese with vanilla.
Slowly add powdered sugar.
Add milk until spreading consistency.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening well.
Add vanilla, then eggs.
Next, add dry ingredients.
Roll and cut in desired shapes.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook whole head of cauliflower, covered in 1-inch boiling, salted water, 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
Melt margarine, add flour and stir in milk, cooking until smooth and thick.
Add salt, pepper, eggs, pimiento and green onion.
Place cauliflower in greased baking dish.
Pour sauce over cauliflower and sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: "rinktum ditty"
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add tomatoes and soda and heat.
Add spices.
Add some of the mixture to the beaten egg, then combine egg mixture with tomato and spice mixture.
As soon as heated again, add grated cheese and heat slowly, just until cheese is melted.
Serve on saltines or toast points.

title: play dough
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Add 2 cups flour.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: pork chops o'brien
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large skillet, heat oil; brown chops on both sides. Drain. Sprinkle chops with seasoned salt; set aside. In a large bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt. Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 2/3 cup onions. Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13 baking dish; arrange pork chops on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until chops are done. Top chops with remaining cheese and 2/3 cup onions; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more or until onions are golden brown.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, cover chicken with water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken.
Reserve broth.
Bone and shred chicken; set aside.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Blend sugars, shortening, oil, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: biscuit barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spray muffin pan with Pam. Brown ground beef until thoroughly cooked. Drain. Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Cook 1 minute to blend flavors. Separate dough into 10 biscuits. Press each to form a 4-inch round circle. Place 1 biscuit in each muffin cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides, forming a 1/4-inch rim. Spoon about 1/4 cup of beef mixture into each biscuit-lined cup. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until edges of biscuits are golden brown. Cool 1 minute; remove from pan. Yield: 10 barbecups.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Mix the pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 7 to 8 minutes until toasted. Set aside to cool.

title: cakeless fruitcake
directions: Mix all items together.
Pack in baking pans tightly.
Cook at 200° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Gets better with age; store in freezer.
Very rich; small slices are ample.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up vegetables and steam until tender in 2 cups water. Drain vegetables and mash with a wooden spoon (save water).
Mix the melted oleo, dressing mix and vegetables.
Add the Velveeta cheese and mix well.
Add the 2 cups reserved water; mix and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: morello's muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add vanilla to milk and egg.
Fold into dry ingredients.
Bake about 20 minutes in 450° oven.
Blueberries, nuts or raisins may be used for variation.

title: mahi mahi vegetable curry
directions: Stir together the curry and flour.
Cube Mahi Mahi in 1-inch pieces.
Add to curry mix and coat well.
Fry in butter and oil until done.
Place on platter and set aside.
Fry onions and garlic.
Add tomatoes and simmer 10 minutes.
Add eggplant and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over Mahi Mahi.

title: ham-broccoli and potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease pie plate (9 x 1/4-inch). Cover potato slices from potato package with boiling water in 2 1/2-quart bowl; stir in salt. Let stand, uncovered, 15 minutes; drain well. Toss potatoes with melted butter and 1 egg. Press potato mixture against bottom and side of pie plate. Bake 10 minutes. Mix ham, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese, 2 eggs and onion. Heat 2 tablespoons margarine in 2-quart saucepan until melted; stir in sauce mix from scalloped potato package, the milk and mustard. Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.

Fold into ham mixture; spoon into potato shell. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Rinse potatoes off and place on oven rack.
Bake until done and skin is hard.
Remove from oven; cut open down middle.
Take spoon and scoop out inside, being careful not to tear skin.
Mix the insides with the rest of ingredients in a large bowl.
Put mixture back into potato skins; place on a cookie sheet.
Put back in oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
In a mixing bowl combine first 6 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients, beating with electric beater until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn into pan or pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes in the 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or until done (for two 9-inch layers, bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes, until done).
Cool on wire rack.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: kids' no bake cookies
directions: In large pan melt both bags of chips.
Stir in noodles; mix together.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheets.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: scrunch
directions: Mix all ingredients except sesame seed.
Spread on sheets in dehydrator.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Dehydrate until firm enough to break into pieces.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Mix sugars, milk and margarine in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Two eggs beaten fine as silk.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes, oleo, salt, pepper, onion and soup; mix well.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: aunt leona's lasagna
directions: Cook noodles, cook
onion, garlic and meat until brown. Add tomato paste and spices;
cook
until
thick.
Arrange
in layers, meat, cheese,
then
Parmesan
cheese, cottage cheese, then meat ending with Parmesan.

title: lemon butter
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar gradually, continuing to beat.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool and store in refrigerator. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: easy day tuna
directions: Mix all in saucepan.
Heat and simmer.
Serve over rice or toast.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Cook hen until done.
Cook noodles in 1/2 the broth.
Cook other ingredients in rest of broth.
Chop hen.
Put hen, sauce and noodles in layers until pan is full.
Put bread crumbs and grated cheese over this.
Bake until bread crumbs brown and cheese melts.

title: no roll butter cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mold dough in ball the size of a walnut.
Press down with a fork or decorative glass bottom.
Top with sugar (colored or white).
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Test a cookie for richness.
May have to add a little more flour.

title: walnut fudge pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa; mix together.
Add eggs; mix well. Add sugar, flour, salt, flavoring and pecans or walnuts.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: mom's cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and baking powder. Add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Melt shortening in iron skillet. Coat sides of skillet and pour excess into batter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle flour into bottom of skillet. Add batter.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes a 5-inch skillet.
(Double for a 9 or 10-inch skillet.)

title: oven barbecued brisket
directions: Season one nice size brisket with Italian fat-free dressing. Pour over 1 small bottle of liquid smoke.
Wrap in foil.
Leave sitting in refrigerator overnight.

title: aunt thelma's  scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, pimientos, butter and all seasonings.
Beat egg slightly and add with the milk and cracker crumbs to the corn.
Mix well and put into a buttered shallow baking dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375 degrees. Serves 6.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Fry steak in iron skillet.
After you put steak in grease, add extra flour on top of steak, enough to make gravy.
Fry until real brown.
Add about a glass of water to make gravy.
If gravy is too thick, add more water.
Add salt and pepper to gravy to taste. Cook on low for about 1 hour to make tender.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Stir to dissolve jello and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in oblong dish. Refrigerate

title: old-fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and butter, mixing until blended.
Add flour, sugar and spices.
Mix well.
Blend in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Continue baking for 40 minutes.

title: curry chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Remove cover and let stand in oven for 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Fold into squash.
Fold in stuffing mix.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: sweeten up your day treats
directions: In a large saucepan, melt at low heat the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips. Stir in peanut butter. Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts, vanilla and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Chill 30 minutes. Makes about 12 treats.

title: holli's pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well.
Lightly grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: rhubarb fritters
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, 1 cup sugar and salt.
In another bowl, whisk egg yolks, milk and butter.
Gradually add to the dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Toss rhubarb with the remaining sugar, gently stir into batter.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
In an electric skillet or deep-fat fryer, heat oil to 375 degrees.
Drop batter by tablespoonful into oil.
Fry, a few at a time, turning with a slotted spoon until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water.
Add sugar, Hawaiian Punch and lemon juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: lemon sunshine cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together until thick. Stir in flour. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Slowly add 1 c. sugar, beating until stiff and glossy peaks form.
Gradually fold yolk mixture into egg whites. Pour into ungreased Teflon coated 10 inch tube pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour. Invert cake to cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take chicken off the bone. Mix in bowl the chicken and both soups.
Fix stuffing as on package.
Then put a layer of stuffing and a layer of meat into a casserole dish.
Repeat until all mixtures are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "ravani" - syrup cake
directions: Beat eggs with oil and sugar until light, 15 to 20 minutes. Mix dry ingredients with cake flour and add to beaten eggs alternately with milk.
Add the vanilla and beat until well mixed. Put in 12 x 9-inch pan and bake in 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Pour cold syrup over hot cake or cool the cake and pour hot syrup on it.
When completely cold, cut into pieces and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thickens.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Beat milk, pudding mix and cream cheese together until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: cheesy bean dip
directions: Blend together with mixer the cream cheese, sour cream, bean dip, taco seasoning and Tabasco sauce.
Mixture must be very creamy.
Then mix in onions and cheese cubes.

title: tuna pie
directions: Mix tuna, cheese and onion together and put in pie shell. Beat eggs.
Add milk and mayonnaise; stir in seasonings.
Spoon mixture over tuna.
(Do not pour all at once.)
Bake at 350° until puffy, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepper nut sandwiches
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Spread on trimmed whole-wheat or white bread.
This yields 5 dozen finger sandwiches.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Boil sugar and Karo until sugar is melted; remove from burner and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add Rice Krispies. Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cool.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Let cool for 15 minutes (pierce top with knife or toothpick).
Pour the following mixture over cake and let soak in:
1 can cream of coconut (Coco Reba). Let completely cool overnight.

title: salsa
directions: Bring to a boil in a pan; simmer 30 minutes or longer until desired thickness. Put into hot sterilized pint canning jars. Process in hot water bath for 15 minutes. You can also put it in a large container and keep for awhile in the refrigerator. This makes 4 pints with some left over.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper, let cool and enjoy.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and flour, then milk.
Melt butter in pan and put berries, then your batter and then add water over top of that. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Cool mixture slightly.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Add eggs, soup, onions, salt and pepper, mayonnaise and cheese.
Put cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 2-quart casserole dish.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix soda with bananas.
Mix sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add bananas to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and other ingredients.
Bake about 1 hour in moderate oven (375°).

title: easy to do cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Dip thinly sliced pieces of liver in flour, salt and pepper. Brown in hot grease.
Add onion (cut up) in liver after it browns. Then add peeled and sliced carrots and potatoes.
Cover and cook until done.
Cook down to make gravy.

title: cabbage slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together in blender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter and mix all ingredients well, adding pecans last.
Line pie pan with pie crust; pour mixture in and bake at moderate 350° or so until solid.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order, in a 2 to 3-quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, longer if refrigerated.
Let set approximately 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken mcnoodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from broth.
Reserve liquid.
Cook noodles in broth until tender, adding water if more liquid is needed.
Remove chicken from bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, noodles, sour cream, soups and salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix stuffing mix with butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Fry salt pork until crisp; drain.
In 2 tablespoons of drippings, brown beef slowly on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt, few grindings of pepper and flour.
Toss to coat evenly.
Place in heavy 2-quart casserole; add salt pork.
To frying pan, add wine, water, herb bouquet and garlic.
Bring to boil; pour over meat. Cover tightly.
Cook in 350° oven until tender, about 2 hours. Skim off all fat.
Saute raw onions and mushrooms in a little of the fat a few minutes.
Add onions to beef; cook 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook 10 minutes.
Adjust seasonings.
Top with parsley.
Serve over noodles or potatoes and your favorite vegetables surrounding it.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Remove skin from chicken.
Place chicken in baking dish with marinade, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, turning chicken occasionally.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several days. Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: raspberry lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until mixture thickens and clears. In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in Eagle Brand, ReaLemon and food coloring if desired.
Pour into crust and bake 8 minutes. Spoon raspberries evenly over top.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Top with whipped topping.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, remove stems and hollow out.
Tear bread into small pieces.
Combine cheese, bread, eggs and salt.
Stuff mixture into mushrooms.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350°, then broil 2 to 3 minutes to brown slightly.

title: french green salad
directions: Rub salad bowl with garlic.
Measure in salt, mustard and paprika.
Grind pepper over; blend.
Beat in salad oil with fork. Add greens.
Toss until leaves glisten.
Sprinkle with vinegar and lemon juice.
Toss again.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine eggs and oil, then mix in the cake mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet with room to spread.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until almost brown.

title: crock-pot beef stew
