directions: Add first four ingredients to crock-pot with 1/2 cup water. Prepare gravy mix according to instructions and add to crock-pot. Cook on high 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Add peas and cook on low for thirty minutes.
Serve on noodles or rice.
May also be served with biscuits.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add all ingredients together in large soup kettle.
Cook slowly for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour half into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place hash browns in dish.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream and salt. (Mixture will be thick.)
Spread mixture over potatoes. Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle with remaining butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna romanoff
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions, pimento, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce in a bowl.
Stir in noodles, tuna and olives and place in greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken tender and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing.
Mix thoroughly.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of a casserole dish and add chicken.
Blend together the 2 cans of soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: rock hard candy
directions: Sprinkle 18x24 inch piece of foil with powdered sugar. Mix next three ingredients in pan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Boil until temperature reaches 310° or until drops of syrup form hard & brittle threads in cold water.
Remove from heat. Stir in flavor and color. Pour onto foil.
Cool. Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 well-greased round foil pans, lightly floured.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: honey-berry frozen yogurt
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
In blender, blend strawberries until smooth.
Add honey, vanilla and yogurt.
Blend again.
Pour into popsicle molds or ice cube tray.
Cover with plastic.
Freeze 1 hour, then add popsicle sticks.
Freeze until solid.

title: mexican fiesta biscuit bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in oven in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Separate dough into 13 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into 8 pieces.
Place biscuit pieces in large bowl.
Toss with 1 3/4 cups salsa.
Spoon evenly into margarine coated dish. Sprinkle with cheese, green pepper, onion and olives.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until edges are deep golden brown and center is set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with salsa.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix milk, juice and Cool Whip; put in pie shell.
Chill before serving.
May be frozen.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in 2 cups water.
In another kettle, add bouillon to 1 cup water.
Melt butter and stir in flour.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milk slowly.
Whip into bouillon and stir until smooth and thick.
Add broccoli, onion and water.
Mix well and stir in cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted. Add salt and pepper.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in water; remove chicken.
Let cool, then remove bones.
To water, add onions, black pepper, bouillon and rice. Let cook until rice is tender.
Add chicken.
Heat until chicken is hot, then it's ready to serve.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine shortening, salt and hot water.
Let stand until cool.
Beat eggs and add sugar, yeast and water mixture.
Stir 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add remaining flour gradually.
Place in bowl; cover and place in refrigerator.

title: church casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, removing fat.
Mix together onion soup mix, egg and bread crumbs.
Pat evenly the ground beef on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add French-style green beans next.
Spread soups on top and then place Tater Tots on top of all just before baking. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Freeze.
When frozen, cut into squares and serve.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients until smooth.
Blend in both sugars. Blend after each remaining ingredient.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add orange juice concentrate, bananas and pineapple, stirring until orange juice is dissolved.
Stir in 7-Up, then pour into large container or several small containers and freeze.
Thaw approximately 1 hour or until slushy before serving.
A breakfast favorite!

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Beat eggs and add sugar and flour.
Gradually add milk to mixture.
Add vanilla, margarine and can of coconut.
Pour into 2 pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.
Makes its own crust.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.

Meanwhile, cook noodles separately and drain. Combine noodles and ground beef in a large bowl with taco seasoning mix and place in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours to chill. Just before serving, combine all ingredients (except sour cream and chips) with meat mixture.
Place crushed tortilla chips on plate. Top with salad and sour cream if desired. Serve salad cold.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are tender in a 350° oven.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add brown sugar and blend.
Add flavorings and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use a tube pan.

title: quick fondant
directions: Put milk and vanilla into mixing bowl.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar.
Mix to smooth rich ball.
Flavor as desired. Shape into patties, fruit rolls, balls covered with coconut, etc. Stuff dates, prunes, figs, etc.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and mix gently.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole; dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti with zucchini
directions: Cook the pasta in a large pan of boiling water, following directions on the packet.
Slice the zucchini into thin rounds. Fry them in hot olive oil until tender.
Stir well.
Add pasta and black pepper.
Now add the grated cheese.
Stir again until all the cheese has melted.
Add fresh basil leaves if available. Serve immediately.

title: good earth salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients for dressing.
Clean lettuce and spinach and tear into bite-size pieces.
Right before serving, toss dressing and greens.
Dice egg and crush bacon and add to dressing.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Stiffly beat egg whites.
Add sugar slowly.
Add Ritz crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream and cocoa.
Spread on cooled pie.
Top with chocolate Cool Whip and chocolate shavings.

title: crispy easter nests
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add noodles and M&M's.
Mix well.
Drop by 1/3 cupfuls onto well-greased cookie sheet, with well-greased fingers, shape into nests.
Refrigerate until firm.
Dust bottoms with powdered sugar.
Fill with peanut M&M's.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes and grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine syrup, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil gently for 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly.
Place pecans in pie shell. Mix eggs, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Gradually stir in cooled syrup mixture.
Pour over pecans in pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar and flour. Stir in cherries. Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Sprinkle with almond extract and dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it. Seal and flute.

Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strips of foil to prevent excessive browning. Remove foil during the last 15 minutes of baking. Bake until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through the slits in crust, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fry in deep frying pan, adding oil as needed.
Each fritter should be the size of a pancake.
Serve immediately.

title: piccalilli relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables and mix.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.
Press to remove excess liquid.
Add sugar, spices and horseradish to vinegar; simmer 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and heat to boiling.
Pack, boiling hot, into hot pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch head space.
Adjust caps.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields 7 pints.

title: potato buffet
directions: In large bowl combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 of the onions.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake, covered for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.

title: texas turtles
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients until well blended (1 minute). Divide batter in half (about 1 1/2 cups).
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes and cool completely.

title: beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut onion, celery and green pepper. Coarsely chop leftover beef in small cubes.
Put beef in 1 tablespoon butter for several minutes (if using ground beef, cook until brown and drain).
Transfer ingredients into medium size casserole dish, putting remaining butter in pan.
Toss in chopped vegetables and cook until limp.
Stir in mushroom soup, water, salt and pepper and mix in beef.
Cover and bake 30 minutes more. Remove; sprinkle surface with Chinese noodles and bake 10 minutes more.
Serve over noodles.

title: luscious cupcakes
directions: Mix first three ingredients, form into balls and press into miniature cupcake tins.
Combine remaining ingredients for the filling.
Spoon into crusts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then reduce to 250° and bake 10 minutes more.
Allow to cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: microwave enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add chili, seasoning mix, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat and add black olives.

title: spicy sherried walnuts
directions: In saucepan, blend brown sugar, sherry, corn syrup, pumpkin spice and salt.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in walnuts until well coated.
Remove and roll in sugar.
Spread on cookie sheet to dry.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Set aside confectioners sugar.
Blend in butter/margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and pecans.
Roll dough in small balls and place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll puffs while hot in confectioners sugar and again when cold.
Yields 2 dozen puffs.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend well.
Spoon into ovenproof baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup toasted sliced almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: vietnamese egg rolls
directions: Mix all and place in egg roll wrappers; seal with beaten egg. Deep fry and can be frozen.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: lemon supreme special cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a tube pan.
Take remaining nectar. Heat and add 1/2 to 3/4 cup powdered sugar.
Spoon over cake.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Pour into baking dish and arrange bacon on top of beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and put in 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Add beef, diced onions and rice.
Pour tomato soup and water over top of mixture.
Bake one hour in 350° oven.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: michael's pizza
directions: Flatten the biscuits and put pizza sauce on them.
Put pepperoni on them and then cheese.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook popcorn.
Place in large brown bag.
Shake old maids to bottom.
Remove popped corn.
In saucepan mix brown sugar, melted butter, syrup and salt; stir together and bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla, then add soda.
Pour and stir together over popped corn.
Spread popped corn over cookie sheet or bread pan. Place in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove.

title: lemon bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Roll into a bar shape. Roll in coconut.
Chill.
Slice into bonbons.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix everything while noodles are boiling.
Drain noodles.
Add to mixture while hot.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In a small bowl stir dry ingredients together to thoroughly mix.
In large measuring cup measure milk and then add egg.
Beat together until egg is completely beaten.
Add to dry ingredients and stir to moisten.
May be a little lumpy.
Pour 1/4 cupfuls onto medium hot griddle that is lightly greased.
Makes 16 (3-inch) pancakes.

title: spicy baked chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken wings.
Pat dry. Arrange in shallow baking dish.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: Rinse beans, cover with water and soak overnight.
Brown ground beef and onion in a small amount of oil.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cook 4 hours or more.
Add water if necessary.

title: new england skillet dinner
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion; cook slowly until tender.
Add carrots, cover and cook over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: california vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together and put in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread the Cheez Whiz on top and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Puree enough strawberries in blender to make 1 cup.
Put in saucepan and heat to boiling.
Cook 1 minute.
Cool.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir in strawberries and chopped nuts.
Pour in 9 x 5 loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour or until center sticks clear.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.
Wrap in foil.
Good spread with strawberry cream cheese.

title: caramel crunch rings
directions: Melt butter. Combine sugar and flour. Stir into butter.
Add water. Cook over low heat to 215°, stirring constantly.
Quickly pour over corn flakes and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into buttered individual ring molds.
Let cool until set.
Turn molds out and fill with ice cream.
Makes 10 rings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix fruit, sugar, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Place in casserole. Mix remaining ingredients, thinning with a little milk if necessary.
Pour on top of fruit. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in mashed bananas. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Blend into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts. Turn into greased and wax paper-lined 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Increase temperature to 350° and bake 15 to 20 minutes more or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salad oil in electric mixer. Grate zucchini (remove seeds and peel).
Sift flour and cinnamon; add dry ingredients to liquid.
Add chopped nuts.
May add raisins and pineapple, if desired.
Pour into buttered loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Simmer water, clam juice, onion, carrots, potatoes and celery until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook about 30 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan with 1 package (1/3 box) graham crackers.
Don't need to crumble or break up.
With electric mixer, whip puddings and 3 cups of milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1/2 pudding mixture on first layer of crackers. Add another layer of graham crackers.
Spoon last half of pudding mixture on second layer of crackers.
Add final layer of graham crackers.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a 2-quart glass casserole, combine noodles and water or wine. Microwave covered on High (max power) for 10 minutes, stirring once.

title: speclasu cookies(german)
directions: In a large bowl of mixer on high, beat butter with brown sugar and egg until mixture is light and fluffy.
Sift flour with spices and salt.
Stir in half the flour mix with almonds.
Mix with hands, if necessary.
Use the other half of the flour to roll dough out to form shapes.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven and cool.
Can be decorated if you like.

title: ellen's yellow squash and green chilies casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 10 minutes after it comes to a boil; drain well.
While still hot, add salt, pepper, garlic powder, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Add green chilies, pimento and eggs. Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over squash mixture. Sprinkle crackers over cheese.
Top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kathryn's filled cookies
directions: Flour to make soft dough.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add milk and soda mixture, baking powder and vanilla. Flour enough to make soft dough. Roll out cookies and cut into desired size.
Drop teaspoonful of cherry pie filling or raisin filling.
Add a little extra sugar if desired before putting on top. After top is put on, press around edges with a fork.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, sugar and vanilla. Beat until it thickens. Add sour cream and Cool Whip; mix until smooth. Put layer of vanilla wafers first, layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding mixture. Continue layers ending with pudding mixture on top.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apples, apple juice and all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Make lattice strips of pie crust on top. Brush top with butter.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa and cut in margarine.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture, press remaining on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweet milk until smooth; add vanilla and egg.
Pour over prepared crust.
Combine nuts with reserved crumb mixture; sprinkle evenly over cheese mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool; chill.
Cut into bars.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and oleo; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, oleo, vanilla and water or milk until it looks like frosting.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas over frosting.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand in a large bowl.
Pour into two 9-inch grease pie plates.

title: sharon's pumpkin pie
directions: Blend last 8 ingredients together.
Put into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes or so.
Cool and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: mexican one dish meal
directions: Brown meat and onion, then drain.
Add soups, milk and Ro-Tel tomatoes to meat mixture in skillet.
Pour over Doritos that have been placed in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Put pretzels on a cookie sheet.
Mix onion soup mix and melted butter together.
Pour over pretzels.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Turn or stir.

title: picante sauce
directions: Seed and chop jalapeno peppers (leave seeds in for hotter sauce).
Combine with bell peppers, green chilies, onion, tomatoes and lime juice in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Store in refrigerator.
(You may use fresh tomatoes instead of canned to make a chunky sauce.)
(If sauce is too hot, add additional tomatoes.)

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, and margarine in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly until it comes to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, vanilla, and chocolate chips.
Blend well.
Add nuts and mix again.
Pour into a greased 9 X 12 pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Serve with Wheat Thins or any kind of crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place into crusts.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sugary apple muffins
directions: Sift flour with baking powder; add salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Next, cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in beaten egg, then flour, alternating with milk.
Fold in apples.
Fill greased muffin tins almost full.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon (mix together).
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 20 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Blend softened margarine, cheese and red pepper.
Add flour and blend well.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Roll to make small balls. Mash with a fork and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "bill's shrimp"
directions: In large pot, put water, onion, celery, bay leaves and juice of 1 lemon.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain shrimp.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat to boiling crushed pineapple, then add orange Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add cheese, mayo and milk.
Mix well.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: sponge cake roll
directions: Line a 10 x 15 x 1-inch baking pan with waxed paper.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Add cream of tartar; continue beating until stiff but not dry. Add sugar, a tablespoonful at a time, while continuing beating. Beat egg yolks with a fork.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Fold yolks into egg whites, mixing well.
Fold in flour by tablespoonfuls. Pour batter into paper lined pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Turn cake at once on a tea towel which has been covered with confectioners sugar.
Quickly peel off waxed paper and cut off any crisp edges.

title: banana-walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 (1/2 cup) muffin cups.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in large bowl. Combine bananas, butter, egg and milk in medium bowl.
Add banana mixture to dry ingredients, mixing with wooden spoon until just combined.
Add walnuts to mixture.
Divide batter into muffin cups.
Bake 25 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave door slightly open for 10 additional minutes if you desire crispy tops. Otherwise, remove and serve warm or at room temperature.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly with whisk until mixture thickens.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool quickly.
Set in pan of ice water.
Stir it.
Cover and refrigerate until completely cooled, overnight.
Fold in whipped cream and sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Combine and heat all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in
foil
lined pan; pour sauce over it and cover with foil.
Cook
in
preheated
350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and allow chicken to brown for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cream cheese dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: dark moist chocolate cake
directions: Cook together the water, margarine and cocoa until bubbles. Remove from heat.
Add sugar; stir well.
Let cool completely. When cool, add eggs, flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.
Use 2 (9-inch) cake pans, a 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan. Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Time may vary, depending on which pan you use.
Enjoy!

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 2 ready pie crusts.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bones and place in baking dish. Pour 2 1/2 to 3 cups broth over chicken.
Melt butter.
Add the flour, buttermilk and black pepper.
Mix and spoon over chicken (this makes the crust).
Bake at 425° for approximately 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into wedges.
In large pan, add water, sugar and 1/2 cup of cinnamon candy.
Add apples; cook until tender.
As you remove apples, add more to cinnamon mixture. If coloring becomes pink in color, add more of the cinnamon candy.
Great with ham.
Cinnamon broth can be saved and served with apple pie.

title: russian apple torte
directions: Soak coarsely grated (good size) apples in rum or lemon juice. Cream the eggs, butter and sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nuts and chocolate.
Add flour and apple mixtures to creamed ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured spring-form pan; bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken of the duke
directions: In large frying pan, fry bacon.
Reserve grease.
Set bacon on woodstove to keep warm.
Add 1/4 cup olive oil to frying pan. Shake the chicken pieces in the flour, salt and pepper.
Fry it in the hot bacon grease and olive oil until very crisp (15 to 20 minutes) over medium heat.
Saute 3 medium onions, cut in wedges, until soft, but not brown.
Add chicken, wine, sugar and thyme leaves.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms and olives; simmer 15 minutes.
Remove to warm serving tray and top with crumbled bacon.

title: captain's casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk and cheese until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Combine rice, oregano and pepper in greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Drain tomatoes, measuring 1/2 cup juice.
Stir juice and water into rice.
Slice tomatoes.
Arrange most of the tomatoes on rice.
Add onion, tuna and olives.
Pour on sauce; sprinkle with potato chips.
Arrange remaining tomatoes on top.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Peel and cut-up vegetables.
Put in crock-pot.
Add beef on top of vegetables and don't stir.
Sprinkle tapioca and seasonings on top of meat.
Pour beef broth and V-8 juice over all.
Cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours on low.
Fifteen minutes before serving, stir stew to mix in tapioca, which will thicken the stew.

title: chili con queso sauce
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, chilies and taco sauce (hot or mild) in a saucepan or top of double boiler.
Melt on low heat or over simmering water, stirring often; add processed cheese and stir occasionally until all cheese is melted.
Add hot water and stir thoroughly.
Serve with raw cauliflower or broccoli or your favorite chips.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 cups.

title: mandarin orange mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice; stir until completely blended.
Add Mandarin oranges; chill at least for 5 hours or overnight.
Unmold onto large plate; garnish with fresh mint leaves and fresh orange slices, if wished.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and sauce.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet; gently brown meatballs.
Remove skillet.
Pour off fat.
Put meat, chili sauce and jelly in skillet stirring constantly until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir thoroughly until coated.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Makes 60.

title: roast turkey in foil
directions: Rub inside of turkey with salt and pepper.
Rub skin with butter.
Fill turkey loosely with stuffing or prepare in a casserole.
Wrap turkey in foil.
Pour wine, brandy and herbs over turkey before closing foil tight.
Roast turkey in hot oven (400°) for 3 1/2 hours.
Fold foil back and roast for 30 minutes or until turkey is brown.

title: chicken breasts with ham
directions: Grease casserole dish or baking pan.
Wrap chicken breasts in bacon.
Place each on top of ham slice in casserole pan, then pour mixture of soup and sour cream over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Place on dry toast and serve.

title: chicken ole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in seasoned water until tender.
Cool; debone.
Tear into bite-size pieces.
Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients except asparagus and almonds.
Simmer sauce until cheese melts.
To assemble, place a layer of chicken in large casserole, a layer of asparagus and a layer of sauce. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8 generously.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with rice and salad.
You can assemble in two casseroles and freeze one for later.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles in salt water.
Remove from heat; drain.
Make white sauce.
Add cheese and butter.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain fat from mixture.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Cover and return to heat to tender pepper and onions.
Add hamburger and noodles into casserole dish, 13 x 9-inch.
Add tomato soup and mix together.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk and soda mixture and beat well.
Add flour; mix until batter is smooth. Drain berries and add to mixture, folding them in gently.
Pour into muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni bake
directions: Cook meat, bell pepper and onion.
Boil macaroni for 5 minutes and drain.
Season meat while cooking.
Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 450° oven.

title: chicken pasta salad with blueberries(lo-fat)
directions: Place green beans between paper towels and squeeze until barely moist.
Combine green beans and next 6 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine yogurt and next 4 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Pour over chicken mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain 1 can of pineapple.
Save juice from one.
Place pineapple in bottom of Pyrex dish. Distribute cheese over pineapple.
Mix flour, sugar and pineapple juice.
Stir well. Fold in with cheese and pineapple, altogether. Crush Ritz crackers and layer on top.
Pour butter on top.
Cook on 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbly.

title: small family dinner rolls
directions: In large Tupperware mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water; stir in sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape down the sides of the bowl with paddle scraper.
Seal.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down dough.
Turn out on pastry sheet.
Press dough flat.
Cut with cutter or shape cloverleaf. Place in tins.
Let rise again.
Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with seed if desired.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: southern fried catfish
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Dip fish in mixture. Roll in cornmeal to coat.
Heat oil to 370°.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pecan pie brownies
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add the flour and stir until smooth.
Mix in the brown sugar and eggs, stirring until well blended.
Turn the heat up to medium and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and pecans and set aside.
Mix the brownies according to the directions and pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon the filling over the brownie mixture and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 24 brownies.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar; add to prepared package of Dream Whip.
Mix well.
Grease glass bowl.
Place a layer of cubed cake on bottom of bowl.
Spread half of cream cheese mixture on cake.
Top with half of the blueberry filling.
Repeat layers again.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots; split in half lengthwise.
Cover with boiling salted water and boil 10 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together sour cream, mushroom soup, milk and Cheddar.
Add hash browns and onions.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and top with melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandmother's congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice and dissolve Jell-O in juice. Cool.
Add other ingredients and mold.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Rub potatoes with oil and bake. Cool. Refrigerate overnight. Cut in half and scoop out chunks.
Freeze potato skins to use later (brown and garnish for appetizers).

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and egg.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour milk.
Fold blueberries into batter mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: brats and taters
directions: Brown brats in skillet on all sides.
Cover with water.
Cut potatoes into spears and place on top of brats.
Sprinkle pepper on potatoes.
Cover skillet and cook slowly until potatoes are done, approximately 20 minutes.
Remove brats and potatoes from liquid.
Slowly add flour to liquid, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Add milk, brats and potatoes in that order and cook slowly until thickened.

title: scampi over pasta
directions: Add all ingredients to hot skillet; cook until shrimp or scallops are done.
Mix with cooked pasta.
Serve hot or cold.

title: banana pudding
directions: Dissolve sugar and flour in cold milk.
Add beaten egg yolks. Let boil 5 minutes.
Let cool and pour over vanilla wafers and sliced bananas which have been put in layers in Pyrex bowl.
Add topping.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
(Salt and pepper to taste.)
Cook noodles.
Add soups and noodles to hamburger and mix well.
Place 1/2 of mixture in large casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spread 1/2 of Mozzarella on hamburger.
Then spread rest of hamburger and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy romaine salad
directions: Spread in a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, eggs, crumbs, milk, Parmesan cheese, onoin, salt and oregano.
Shape into a loaf and place in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until no pink remains; drain.
Spoon pizza sauce over loaf and top with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Return to the oven for 10 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Meanwhile, if desired, saute green pepper and mushrooms in butter; arrange on top of meat loaf.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef while heating tomato juice and chili beans in pan together.
When ground beef is done, add chili seasoning and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add to juice and beans and bring to almost a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: maple syrup
directions: Boil sugar and water 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in maple flavoring and a little corn syrup, if desired.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°, until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup muffin pan with shortening, or use paper muffin cup liners.
Put shortening and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Cream until soft and fluffy.
Break egg into bowl; beat well with spoon.
Stir flour and baking powder; add to mixture and stir.
Add milk and vanilla; beat until batter is smooth.
Pour into muffin pan, filling each halfway. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan to finish cooling.
Makes 12.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Bake the sweet potatoes for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° (depends on size) until tender.
While hot slice potatoes in half and pour the melted butter, sugar and cinnamon mixture over the centers.
Serve.

title: carol's cake
directions: Fold together and spread.

title: caesar salad
directions: Just before serving, rub large salad bowl with cut clove of garlic.
Tear romaine into bite size pieces.
Squeeze juice from lemon over romaine.
In blender, mix oil, Worcestershire sauce, seasonings, anchovies and coddled egg, as well as 1/4 clove of garlic.
Blend thoroughly; pour over romaine.
Toss until leaves are well coated.
Sprinkle with croutons and cheese.
Serves 6.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into pie crust.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.
Cool before serving.

title: "messy" potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 12 to 14.
